1
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:09,926
<i>Do you guys tend to eat fast?</i>

2
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,137
I'm a slow eater.

3
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:13,722
I practically inhale food.

4
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,934
Those who cook for you
would be happy to see that.

5
00:00:18,017 --> 00:00:19,894
-Well, I do eat with gusto.
-Yeah, you do.

6
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:22,647
-I can really put food away.
-Since you inhale food.

7
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,774
<i>Oh, a new female eternal single.</i>

8
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,068
Oh, someone's…

9
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:33,533
Hello.

10
00:00:33,616 --> 00:00:34,492
<i>What?</i>

11
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,495
-Hello.
-Hello.

12
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:38,872
She's so pretty.

13
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:40,290
She's a total city girl.

14
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:41,791
-There's no seat.
-Where should I…

15
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,793
Are you okay with sitting in the middle?

16
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:45,295
Sure.

17
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,799
-Hello.
-Nice to meet you.

18
00:00:54,053 --> 00:00:55,722
What's your name?

19
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:56,765
Right. I'm…

20
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:58,850
An Jeong-eun.

21
00:00:58,933 --> 00:00:59,934
An Jeong-eun.

22
00:01:00,018 --> 00:01:01,186
This was unexpected.

23
00:01:01,269 --> 00:01:03,396
<i>Gosh, she's gorgeous!</i>

24
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:07,567
<i>Hello. I'm An Jeong-eun,</i>
<i>a 30-year-old eternal single.</i>

25
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:09,235
<i>Oh, Jeong-eun.</i>

26
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,695
I'm her Cupid.

27
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:12,864
-I see.
-Yeah.

28
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:15,366
When Season One came out,

29
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:18,036
I was in the room, and my mom said,
"Hey, that's you on TV."

30
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:21,915
I came out of the room
and asked her what she meant.

31
00:01:21,998 --> 00:01:23,583
Then I saw the title.

32
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:27,587
I've actually been contacted
by <i>My Sibling's Romance</i>

33
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:30,215
-and <i>Heart Signal</i>.
-<i>Really?</i>

34
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:33,176
But my family was like,
"What can you even do there?"

35
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,347
"You'd just be goofing around there
and nothing else."

36
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:39,432
But they said I could pull off this show.

37
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,309
My brother said, "This show is for you."

38
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:45,104
If I'd wanted to become famous,

39
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:49,150
I wouldn't have chosen this show.

40
00:01:49,234 --> 00:01:51,402
I don't mean to throw shade at this show.

41
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:53,988
Why? What's wrong with our show?

42
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:57,242
Did you just turn 30 years old?

43
00:01:57,325 --> 00:01:58,159
Right.

44
00:01:58,243 --> 00:01:59,953
Since you're in your thirties,

45
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:02,914
you must have different kinds of worries.

46
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:04,499
To be honest,

47
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:07,210
I've been told by others

48
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:09,295
that I seem to put up a wall

49
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:12,590
before becoming very close to someone.

50
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:16,886
Why? Regarding which aspect
of your true self?

51
00:02:18,888 --> 00:02:20,932
Back in school…

52
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:24,227
I wasn't a complete outcast,
but I got bullied.

53
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:26,146
A lot of kids hated me

54
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:28,231
and would have the wrong idea about me.

55
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:31,192
Meeting someone new feels like

56
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:33,778
getting one more person who may judge me.

57
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:37,991
You stayed composed
as you told your story, but…

58
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:40,910
People who struggled
with personal relationships in the past,

59
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:43,371
especially in their school days,

60
00:02:43,454 --> 00:02:46,332
often find it difficult to start
romantic relationships later on.

61
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:50,044
In your school days, there's no way
out of those relationships.

62
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:52,922
You couldn't shake off or end
the relationships even if you wanted to.

63
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:56,843
You're scared something similar
would happen in your dating life too.

64
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:59,304
<i>When it comes to relationships,</i>

65
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:03,016
I worry about things
that could happen in the distant future.

66
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:07,520
I promised myself
not to do that this time.

67
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:08,688
Instead of running away,

68
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:11,232
I'll be my authentic self

69
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:12,525
and face my fear head-on.

70
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:14,861
AN JEONG-EUN
TODAY'S TO-DO ITEM: DATING

71
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,154
<i>Jeong-eun.</i>

72
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:18,448
She has a beautiful smile.

73
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,909
-She looks intelligent.
-I know.

74
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:25,330
-It's awkward.
-I know, it is.

75
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:27,582
-It was so unexpected.
-We weren't expecting you.

76
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:28,499
I know.

77
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,835
Have you gotten close with each other?

78
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,837
We were about to speak
to each other casually.

79
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:35,089
-I see.
-We were just about to do that.

80
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:36,799
-That's the vibe now?
-Yes.

81
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:39,469
-Then may I speak casually too?
-Please go ahead.

82
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:40,803
Shall I do that?

83
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:42,388
Yes, go ahead.

84
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:43,973
Feel free to talk casually.

85
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:47,310
<i>I was taken aback.</i>

86
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:51,314
I just thought,
"We keep getting pretty ladies here."

87
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:52,982
-Wow.
<i>-Gosh.</i>

88
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,984
Seung-hyun is crushing on every woman.

89
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:58,446
-Seung-hyun falls in love too quickly.
-I'm sorry, but he's like…

90
00:03:58,529 --> 00:04:00,531
-He fell for her, right?
-I think so.

91
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,116
-He's quick to fall in love.
-He is.

92
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:05,828
I didn't expect to meet
this many people so suddenly.

93
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,872
I'm very flustered.

94
00:04:08,539 --> 00:04:09,832
We'll do all the talking.

95
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:10,833
Thank you.

96
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,835
<i>-Way to go, Jin-woo.</i>
<i>-Jin-woo is taking the lead.</i>

97
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:15,088
-Would you like water or cola?
-Water, please.

98
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:16,589
Sure.

99
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:18,049
We were speaking casually, right?

100
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,301
He isn't coming on too strong.

101
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:23,721
Are you an introvert or an extrovert?

102
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:25,515
-I'm a total introvert.
-A total introvert?

103
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:28,101
Yes. I get shy around strangers.

104
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:29,602
You seem like…

105
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,604
a thinker.

106
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:33,606
INTJ?

107
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:35,650
-FJ?
-I'm ISTP.

108
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,193
TP? I see.

109
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,695
If you're interested in MBTI,

110
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:41,489
you must know ISTPs aren't known
for having a good personality.

111
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:43,741
I've also read about that.

112
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:46,619
We have a reputation for being rude.

113
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,621
I don't read too much into it.

114
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:50,832
I'm just curious about general traits.

115
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:53,584
-She keeps talking to Jin-woo, right?
-She is.

116
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,004
Everyone has strengths and weaknesses.

117
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:58,715
I was only interested in MBTI
as a tool to understand people better.

118
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:00,508
That's a good mindset.

119
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:05,888
<i>What caught my eye first was her looks.</i>

120
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:08,016
But she was very well-spoken too.

121
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,476
<i>It made me want to talk to her more.</i>

122
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:16,149
-Why are they making you sit with us?
-I guess I was clueless.

123
00:05:16,232 --> 00:05:18,735
It would've been funny, but still.

124
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,486
<i>-Hyuk-joon seems a bit…</i>
<i>-Why?</i>

125
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:21,612
<i>I don't remember much.</i>

126
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,114
<i>Honestly, I was a bit upset.</i>

127
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:25,825
After all, a new female participant meant

128
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:27,869
there'd be a new male participant as well.

129
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:30,621
It got me worried.

130
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:33,708
Hyuk-joon is devoted.

131
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,669
-Hyun-seo must be on his mind.
-He's convicted for sure.

132
00:05:38,671 --> 00:05:39,797
<i>Was it fun?</i>

133
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,133
It was no joke.

134
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:44,302
-We were turning and stuff.
-That's right.

135
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:46,012
We held hands and did this.

136
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:50,683
Here he comes.

137
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,185
-Male game changer.
-Here he comes.

138
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:55,646
<i>I like his silhouette.</i>

139
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:57,231
Code Red, guys.

140
00:05:57,982 --> 00:05:59,067
Game changer danger.

141
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,581
<i>-He's handsome.</i>
<i>-He's a stunner.</i>

142
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,462
Hello.

143
00:06:19,962 --> 00:06:21,756
-Hello.
-Hi.

144
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,174
Holy moly. Hold on.

145
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:24,258
<i>She said, "Holy moly."</i>

146
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:25,426
<i>-She's flustered.</i>
<i>-Soo-hyun!</i>

147
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:34,727
Nice to meet you.

148
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,604
-Hello.
-Nice to meet you.

149
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,900
<i>He had a very likable face.</i>

150
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:43,402
<i>I thought he was put-together</i>
<i>and handsome.</i>

151
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,363
<i>I thought, "Gosh, he's really tall."</i>

152
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:49,117
"How… Gosh." This was my initial reaction.

153
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:57,125
Hello. I'm Kim Tae-hoon,
a 29-year-old eternal single.

154
00:06:58,042 --> 00:06:59,919
<i>-Tae-hoon.</i>
<i>-Wow.</i>

155
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,673
-He's handsome.
-He's a stunner.

156
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:04,882
ARE YOU AN ETERNAL SINGLE?

157
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:07,051
I don't think of myself as one,

158
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:10,471
but that's what other people call me.

159
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:15,351
I dated someone in middle school.

160
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,727
But my friends say

161
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:20,398
it doesn't count
because we were too young.

162
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:23,276
The relationship you had in middle school…

163
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:24,235
Does that count?

164
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:25,820
-You know…
-It lasted two months.

165
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:28,406
They didn't meet up once after becoming
official if I remember correctly.

166
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:31,159
No, I have nice and warm memories of her.

167
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:34,203
Hold on. "Warm"? Did you ever touch her?

168
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,955
-Did you ever hold her hand?
-Don't be silly.

169
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:36,914
You didn't, right?

170
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,708
-No.
-He never even held her hand.

171
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,710
-Those memories aren't real.
-Hold on.

172
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:41,711
<i>"They're not real."</i>

173
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:43,421
There was no physical touch at all.

174
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:45,965
We mostly talked at school

175
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,426
or talked on messenger.

176
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,636
WHY DID YOU BREAK UP?

177
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:54,265
I pursued her first,
and we started dating,

178
00:07:54,348 --> 00:07:56,851
but the return value wasn't
as big as I expected.

179
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,603
-"Return value"?
-That's his buzzword.

180
00:07:58,686 --> 00:07:59,937
-"Return value"?
-Yes.

181
00:08:00,521 --> 00:08:01,522
What did you expect?

182
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:04,734
I thought we'd be
all lovey-dovey and stuff,

183
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:09,113
but we barely talked
when we actually met up.

184
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:13,409
I guess I expect
a high return from the woman I date.

185
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:17,830
He wants to receive as much as he gives.
That's his mindset.

186
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,373
-He wants it to be give-and-take.
-Yes.

187
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,792
But such a mindset
would pull you away from dating.

188
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:22,877
You're right.

189
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:23,920
WHY DIDN'T YOU DATE AGAIN?

190
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,379
In high school,

191
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:28,883
I got into a fight with a girl every year.

192
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,468
-What?
-You got into a fight?

193
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:33,554
The line on the school desk…
We were in 12th grade.

194
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:34,764
In 12th grade?

195
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:37,266
My desk mate complained about me
crossing into her space.

196
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:40,269
I got annoyed and snapped at her,
and she called me a jerk.

197
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:43,856
-She called me petty.
-"Petty."

198
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,484
She said I got on her nerves
when she was on edge.

199
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,695
Don't students stop
drawing a line on the desk

200
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:51,739
-after elementary school?
-You're right.

201
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:55,660
If we were to rate him on a danger scale,
he'd be a 2.5 out of 3.

202
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:56,869
-Out of three?
-Yes.

203
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:59,997
When you get into a fight with a friend,
do you tend to win?

204
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,500
It's ridiculous to talk about
who won, but still.

205
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:06,045
I guess I lose in the end
because I get a bad reputation.

206
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:09,549
Even if you win the argument,

207
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:12,218
-you become the loser.
-Okay.

208
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:14,428
Take the carrot-and-stick approach.

209
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,556
Make sure to speak your mind,

210
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,349
but end it with a compliment.

211
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:20,142
-Okay. End it with a compliment?
-Yes.

212
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:21,269
Shall we try it?

213
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:22,395
Go ahead and eat.

214
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,188
Hey, you punk!

215
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:26,983
What are you, a pig?

216
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,317
Are you happy stuffing yourself?

217
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,236
But you know what? You're cool.

218
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,948
That's just a comedy skit.

219
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:36,951
-I've seen something like that on TV.
-Seriously.

220
00:09:37,034 --> 00:09:38,869
-Episode 146 of <i>Comedy Big League</i>.
-Yes.

221
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,288
You're cool, dude.

222
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:43,124
You're healthy
because you eat so much, you punk.

223
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:44,542
How was that?

224
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:45,710
Right. Like that…

225
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:47,295
-Just give compliments.
-Okay.

226
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:49,463
Try it on me.

227
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,841
Hey, don't eat like that.

228
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,259
What?

229
00:09:53,342 --> 00:09:55,720
-Don't gobble up your food.
-"Gobble up"?

230
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:58,472
But watching you eat makes me happy.

231
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:00,057
He's actually good!

232
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:01,892
I guess that's right.

233
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,936
People say watching me eat
makes them happy.

234
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,062
See? Problem resolved.

235
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:07,565
I nearly got angry
but immediately cooled down.

236
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:08,941
That's it.

237
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,528
Well, we kept joking around,

238
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,864
but when you express
your feelings to a woman,

239
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:16,407
you should be completely honest.

240
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:18,117
-Okay.
-I hope you'll do a great job.

241
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,327
Okay, thank you.

242
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,455
DID YOU TELL YOUR FAMILY
THAT YOU'LL BE ON THE SHOW?

243
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:25,124
They didn't know that I'd applied.
I told them after I got in.

244
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:27,168
My younger sibling told me,
"Cut the crap."

245
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:29,045
My mom and dad told me,

246
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:31,255
"Don't get cocky."

247
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,341
You'll make a great pair with Han-ju!

248
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:34,925
You're right.

249
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:38,554
YOUR RESOLUTION AS A GAME CHANGER

250
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:39,639
I'll do my best

251
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:42,266
to stir things up.

252
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,977
-Hello.
-Nice to meet you.

253
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,437
KIM TAE-HOON
RETURN VALUE IS A MUST

254
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,813
Nice to meet you.

255
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:50,483
I joined the show a bit late,

256
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,610
-so I'm very nervous.
-He's nervous.

257
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:56,322
Is there a reason why you joined late?

258
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:58,366
They just told me to join late.

259
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,659
-Is that so?
-Yes.

260
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:05,956
What have you been up to?

261
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,042
We played paintball.

262
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:09,794
We went partner dancing.

263
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,089
Between paintball and partner dancing,

264
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:14,715
which one would you have picked?

265
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:18,803
I would've picked paintball.

266
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,598
Partner dancing would've been hideous.

267
00:11:22,681 --> 00:11:24,308
I wouldn't have wanted to do that.

268
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:25,393
"Hideous"?

269
00:11:25,476 --> 00:11:26,394
Hold on a second.

270
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:27,770
He has no filter whatsoever.

271
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:28,979
-In a way, he's…
-No, he doesn't.

272
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,606
-"Hideous"?
-He's too straightforward.

273
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:34,068
But I just did that activity.

274
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:36,278
-Your words hurt.
-I guess we were hideous.

275
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:42,576
We don't know each other's ages, so…

276
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:43,744
That's right.

277
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:45,037
Shall we speak casually?

278
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:46,539
-Sure.
-Okay.

279
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,457
What's your ideal type?

280
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,794
She just needs to look pretty in my eyes.

281
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:54,422
Can you cook?

282
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:56,882
Well, I try to cook.

283
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:58,384
Are you a homebody or a socializer?

284
00:11:58,467 --> 00:11:59,635
A total homebody.

285
00:11:59,718 --> 00:12:00,970
What's your favorite liquor?

286
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:02,638
I like <i>makgeolli</i>.

287
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:04,056
Do you travel often?

288
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,518
I find it difficult
to actually decide to go on a trip.

289
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:09,770
So, I don't travel often.

290
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:11,605
What else should we ask?

291
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,899
Or anything you want to ask us?

292
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:16,068
Well, you know…

293
00:12:18,946 --> 00:12:22,116
Figuratively speaking,
it feels like five sisters-in-law

294
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:23,868
are interviewing me.

295
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:24,994
Oh my.

296
00:12:25,077 --> 00:12:27,204
-What are you talking about?
-"Sisters-in-law"?

297
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:28,581
"Sisters-in-law"?

298
00:12:29,957 --> 00:12:31,375
He compared them to sisters-in-law.

299
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:34,170
What on earth is he saying?

300
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,629
He's…

301
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,506
definitely an eternal single.

302
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:40,259
His friends were right.

303
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:42,303
Did he compare this situation
to an interview

304
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:43,929
-with five sisters-in-law?
-Exactly.

305
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:46,348
It was so unnecessary.

306
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,143
Do whatever you want.

307
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:50,144
His score really is 2.5.

308
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:52,730
-He should do what he wants.
-It really is a Code Red situation.

309
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,690
-"Sisters-in-law"?
-"Sisters-in-law"?

310
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:56,942
What are you talking about?

311
00:12:57,026 --> 00:13:01,447
He said he felt like he was
being interviewed by sisters-in-law.

312
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:04,241
Since he newly joined,

313
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:08,204
we asked him a lot of questions
to help him feel included.

314
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:10,789
But I guess he felt like
he was being nagged.

315
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:15,002
Since he was a game changer,
I wondered if he'd take us by storm.

316
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,379
But his energy is too weak
for a game changer.

317
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:22,092
I have a feeling that he and Han-ju
are going to come to blows.

318
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:26,889
Kim Tae-hoon and Lee Han-ju
will have a fistfight.

319
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:29,850
-The producers will need to break them up.
-They'll need to get involved.

320
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:33,270
<i>We're here.</i>

321
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:35,648
<i>-I see their car.</i>
<i>-They're already here.</i>

322
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:37,066
<i>You're right.</i>

323
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:38,943
<i>Then they must be sitting inside together.</i>

324
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:43,364
Drumroll.

325
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:45,407
Stay at the very back. We'll hide you.

326
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,578
I heard the car door getting closed.

327
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:50,621
Are they here?

328
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:52,248
Oh, they're here.

329
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:56,460
They're sitting down.

330
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:57,836
-Is she here? No way.
-She's here.

331
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,464
-There's someone new, right?
-No way!

332
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,132
There's a new person.

333
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,138
Another man is here.

334
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:09,848
<i>They're on edge.</i>

335
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:16,814
-Hello.
-Hey.

336
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:18,566
Hello.

337
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:20,651
-Hi.
-Hello.

338
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:22,486
-Hello.
-Hello.

339
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:25,489
<i>Another pretty girl joined us.</i>

340
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:27,199
<i>I got a bit wary.</i>

341
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:31,245
<i>She was beautiful, so she put me on edge.</i>

342
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:38,627
<i>I thought he was so handsome,</i>
<i>you know, like an actor.</i>

343
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,963
<i>He was cool.</i>

344
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:44,633
And he was about 3 cm taller than me.

345
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:47,094
It made me go, "This is bad."

346
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:49,722
The new guy didn't make me wary.

347
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:53,893
Rather, I wondered if I should
run over and tend to him.

348
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:55,769
Just stay put, Jae-seo.

349
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,608
Hey, there.

350
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:01,775
There's a hand warmer.

351
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:03,694
Thank you.

352
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:06,822
He lit up. Instantly smiling.

353
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:08,157
<i>She sat next to me.</i>

354
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:11,702
<i>I hoped that she would, and she did.</i>

355
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:14,705
<i>Seung-hyun was there too,</i>
<i>but she sat next to me.</i>

356
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,875
I took it as a sign
that she enjoyed our date today.

357
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:19,919
<i>I was over the moon.</i>

358
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,421
-It's packed.
-Yes.

359
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,257
-It really is packed.
-It's crowded here now.

360
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:30,804
-What did you have for dinner?
-We had abalone risotto and…

361
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,307
-Do you like it?
-Sounds delicious. Yes.

362
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,142
We also had pasta.

363
00:15:35,225 --> 00:15:37,102
We had pasta and steak as well.

364
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:38,687
I see. Pasta and steak.

365
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,815
Looks like we both had
typical blind date food.

366
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:43,901
It's awkward, right?

367
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,612
-He's our host again.
-Hello. I'm your host,

368
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,406
-Kim Jae-seo.
-Nice to meet you.

369
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:51,241
-Hello.
-Don't be the host.

370
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:52,159
Jae-seo, focus on dating.

371
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:54,995
-Stop being the host.
-Exactly.

372
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:59,124
In most cases, the game changers
begin by explaining

373
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:01,418
