374
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:02,920
Is there anything unusual to share?

375
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,007
For me…

376
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:08,300
-Oh, let me speak casually.
-Okay.

377
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:11,303
When I was in ninth grade…

378
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:15,307
I dated someone for about 50 days.

379
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:16,725
That was the first and last time.

380
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:22,272
I also have a short dating experience

381
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:26,235
which lasted for about three weeks.

382
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,780
The three with dating experience
are sitting together.

383
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:31,281
You're right.

384
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:33,409
The special cases have gathered around.

385
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:36,620
It's like when you pretend to
hand over a plate…

386
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,247
We got a text.

387
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,293
TODAY IS THE JOB REVEAL DAY
REVEAL YOUR JOB, BUT NOT YOUR AGE

388
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:44,878
<i>-Revealing their jobs.</i>
<i>-Jobs. Good.</i>

389
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:45,963
<i>Okay.</i>

390
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:48,716
Just the job.

391
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,509
-Just the job.
-Nothing else.

392
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:53,971
Revealing their jobs
could make them more attractive.

393
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,265
Let's guess each other's job
before the reveal.

394
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:58,267
-That sounds like fun.
-Right. Let's do that.

395
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:00,936
We said Han-ju could be

396
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,646
-an English teacher.
-An English teacher.

397
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:04,773
HAN-JU

398
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,358
My guess was a flight attendant.

399
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:08,360
That's right. It suits her.

400
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:12,072
I'm a Korean medicine doctor
with two years under my belt.

401
00:17:12,906 --> 00:17:14,283
How cool!

402
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:19,413
-That's so unexpected.
-A Korean medicine doctor.

403
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,624
The two of them have to reveal their jobs

404
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,293
-when they only just got here.
-Yeah.

405
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:25,419
They only just got here.

406
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:26,879
A kindergarten teacher?

407
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:28,547
She has a teacher's vibe.

408
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:31,216
A zookeeper?

409
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:34,053
-A zookeeper.
-That could be a possibility.

410
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:35,387
-You're right.
-Yeah.

411
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:36,722
That isn't it.

412
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:39,850
I'm…

413
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:43,228
a Korean medicine doctor.

414
00:17:44,813 --> 00:17:45,647
Really?

415
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:47,649
I'm a Korean medicine doctor.

416
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:50,069
What's going on?

417
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,613
Really?

418
00:17:58,243 --> 00:17:59,870
Same as Han-ju.

419
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:03,082
<i>I studied Korean Medicine</i>
<i>at Kyung Hee University,</i>

420
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,417
<i>and I've been</i>
<i>a Korean medicine doctor for five years.</i>

421
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:07,711
The disc is back here.

422
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,339
The condition occurs when it protrudes
and presses down the nerves.

423
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:13,217
What I suspect is
an inflammation on this side.

424
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:18,555
<i>I'm always at home or at work.</i>
<i>That's all there is to my daily life.</i>

425
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:23,393
<i>And I tend to do</i>
<i>work-related studies in my spare time.</i>

426
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,021
AN JEONG-EUN, KOREAN MEDICINE DOCTOR

427
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:27,272
She's cool.

428
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,400
When I heard Han-ju's job, I went, "What?"

429
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,860
-It made me happy.
-What a coincidence.

430
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,614
<i>I was very surprised.</i>

431
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,866
<i>I thought this might put us</i>

432
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,120
<i>in the same lane.</i>

433
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:44,081
Since we have the same job,

434
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:45,582
I became wary of her.

435
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,794
-Oh, she's a bit wary.
-She's keeping her in check?

436
00:18:48,877 --> 00:18:51,130
If I were in Han-ju's shoes,
I'd be worried too.

437
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:54,258
<i>There were two Korean medicine doctors.</i>

438
00:18:54,341 --> 00:18:57,344
<i>It was quite unexpected,</i>
<i>so they were the most memorable.</i>

439
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,347
<i>They both looked pretty young,</i>

440
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:03,100
<i>but they have a job</i>
<i>that requires years of studying.</i>

441
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:08,147
It made me think,
"They might be older than I thought."

442
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,356
LEE JIN-WOO
26-YEAR-OLD ETERNAL SINGLE

443
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,567
It's my turn.

444
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:12,568
<i>I'm curious about Jin-woo.</i>

445
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:15,737
He's the arm-wrestling king.

446
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,534
Are you perhaps a personal trainer?

447
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:23,162
-Maybe he has a fitness-related job.
-Fitness.

448
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:24,955
Is he in sports?

449
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,499
I'm a university student.

450
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:31,044
I study Architectural Engineering.

451
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,546
That's cool.

452
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:36,258
<i>I'm currently majoring</i>
<i>in Architectural Engineering</i>

453
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:38,468
<i>at Ajou University.</i>

454
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,220
<i>I'm a university student</i>
<i>in my fourth year.</i>

455
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:42,639
<i>In the Architectural Engineering</i>
<i>department,</i>

456
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:47,311
<i>I'm learning about constructing</i>
<i>and maintaining buildings.</i>

457
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:49,479
<i>At the moment, I'm preparing to find a job</i>

458
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:51,607
<i>at an architecture-related</i>
<i>public enterprise.</i>

459
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:53,775
LEE JIN-WOO, UNIVERSITY STUDENT

460
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,319
<i>He's an architecture student.</i>

461
00:19:58,405 --> 00:19:59,364
JAE-SEO

462
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,617
-Take a guess.
-Let's guess.

463
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,659
An opera singer.

464
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:04,828
An opera singer? Because of my voice?

465
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,663
"An opera singer."

466
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,123
He does have a baritone voice.

467
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,791
I guess she liked his baritone voice.

468
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,919
-We mentioned a musical actor.
-A musical actor.

469
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:13,170
A musical actor!

470
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:18,425
No one got it right.

471
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,471
I'm a game developer.

472
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:26,767
The game is <i>PUBG: Battlegrounds</i>.

473
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:28,560
That's amazing!

474
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:29,478
<i>PUBG: Battlegrounds</i>.

475
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:32,064
-Whoa, that's amazing!
-Oh my!

476
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,359
Really?

477
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:37,611
-Whoa, that's amazing!
-Oh my!

478
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,738
That's insane.

479
00:20:39,821 --> 00:20:42,407
<i>I didn't see that coming, seriously.</i>

480
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:46,828
<i>I've actually played the game</i>
<i>he developed many times.</i>

481
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:49,122
<i>So I found him really cool.</i>

482
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:53,669
PUBG: Battlegrounds<i> is a game</i>
<i>everyone has heard of.</i>

483
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:55,003
<i>It's so well-known.</i>

484
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:58,632
He's one of the creators,
so I felt honored to meet him.

485
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,802
<i>It was totally unexpected.</i>

486
00:21:01,885 --> 00:21:04,596
<i>Honestly, all of us thought</i>
<i>Jae-seo was a musical actor.</i>

487
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:08,308
He seemed like someone
who'd get up and sing "Who is the Sinner?"

488
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:11,061
<i>It was very unexpected.</i>

489
00:21:12,312 --> 00:21:13,981
What a surprise.

490
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:15,649
I don't look it, do I?

491
00:21:16,858 --> 00:21:19,569
-I was sure he's an opera singer.
-Yeah, a singer.

492
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:22,239
I didn't take you
for a Korean medicine doctor either.

493
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:25,200
I'm…

494
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:27,160
I don't have a single clue.

495
00:21:27,869 --> 00:21:31,039
At a multinational insurance corporation,

496
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:34,710
-I do B2B partnerships work.
-Impressive.

497
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:38,755
<i>I graduated from Ewha Womans University</i>

498
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:41,925
<i>with a degree in Architectural</i>
<i>and Urban Systems Engineering.</i>

499
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:44,803
<i>Currently at AXA,</i>

500
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:47,639
<i>I do B2B sales.</i>

501
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:52,769
<i>I help with communication</i>
<i>between companies.</i>

502
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:55,564
JEON SEO-YOON, EMPLOYEE
AT A MULTINATIONAL INSURANCE CORPORATION

503
00:21:55,647 --> 00:21:57,065
That's cool.

504
00:21:57,858 --> 00:22:00,110
Jae-seo's going to fall for her harder.

505
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,321
-I'm next.
-Yes.

506
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:03,655
JUNG-YUN

507
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,324
I'm a university student.

508
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,117
And…

509
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:10,996
I'm majoring in Business.

510
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:17,461
<i>I'm studying Business at Inha University.</i>

511
00:22:17,544 --> 00:22:19,254
<i>I'll be graduating soon.</i>

512
00:22:20,797 --> 00:22:23,592
<i>I've met all my credit requirements,</i>

513
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:26,303
<i>so I go to the library on weekdays</i>

514
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:29,681
<i>to read books or study.</i>

515
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:32,392
<i>I bet his juniors love him.</i>

516
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:33,852
YOON JUNG-YUN, UNIVERSITY STUDENT

517
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:38,190
-Shall I go?
-Sure.

518
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:39,107
I'm…

519
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:42,444
a ceramicist.

520
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:44,112
I can see that.

521
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,322
It suits you.

522
00:22:45,405 --> 00:22:48,825
I studied Art in the UK.

523
00:22:48,909 --> 00:22:50,494
I majored in illustration.

524
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:54,831
Now, my work is a mix
of illustration and pottery.

525
00:22:54,915 --> 00:22:56,374
-She gives off an artist vibe.
-Yes.

526
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:58,085
-It suits you.
-It really does.

527
00:22:58,710 --> 00:23:00,253
-That's cool.
-Thanks.

528
00:23:00,837 --> 00:23:03,215
<i>My first reaction was, "Whoa."</i>

529
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,967
<i>I thought it fits her.</i>

530
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,386
What do you think my job is?

531
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,222
But we know too little about you.

532
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:11,890
-Yeah.
-Then I'll reveal it.

533
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:13,433
You look like an actor.

534
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,436
That's very kind of you.

535
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,314
Well, I'm also…

536
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:22,400
a university student.

537
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:25,153
-What's your major?
-It's

538
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,781
not STEM.

539
00:23:27,864 --> 00:23:30,242
-"Not STEM"? What is it?
-"Not STEM"?

540
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:31,201
Why is he…

541
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:33,578
-Are you kidding me?
-Don't end the conversation there.

542
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:35,914
Hey, I was on the non-STEM track
at Bugae High School too.

543
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:37,374
They didn't ask him if he's

544
00:23:37,457 --> 00:23:38,917
-a STEM major or not.
-What the?

545
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:41,878
<i>Look at their faces.</i>

546
00:23:41,962 --> 00:23:43,672
<i>Everyone is dumbfounded.</i>

547
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:46,341
-Can't you reveal your major?
-Yes, you can.

548
00:23:46,424 --> 00:23:47,300
Oh, you can, but…

549
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:50,011
To be specific,
I'm majoring in Public Policy.

550
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:52,139
-I see.
-Public Policy…

551
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:55,976
<i>I'm studying Public Policy</i>
<i>at Dankook University.</i>

552
00:23:56,977 --> 00:24:00,814
<i>I studied to become a police officer</i>
<i>for about four to five years.</i>

553
00:24:01,565 --> 00:24:05,026
<i>But now, I'm thinking about becoming</i>
<i>a tax accountant or a judicial scrivener.</i>

554
00:24:06,319 --> 00:24:09,573
KIM TAE-HOON, UNIVERSITY STUDENT

555
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:14,536
HYUK-JOON

556
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:15,871
This is a bit nerve-racking.

557
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,164
-Right?
-I'm nervous.

558
00:24:19,207 --> 00:24:20,375
I'm…

559
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:22,043
Well,

560
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,838
I'm a marketer at a distribution company.

561
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:32,053
<i>I'm working as a marketer</i>
<i>at a distribution company.</i>

562
00:24:33,096 --> 00:24:37,184
<i>I direct product photography</i>
<i>to showcase products in the best light.</i>

563
00:24:37,767 --> 00:24:40,145
Please adjust the light
to get rid of that glare.

564
00:24:40,228 --> 00:24:43,815
There's too much text in the background.
Please erase all of them later.

565
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:47,235
<i>I'm in charge of all integrated marketing.</i>

566
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,863
<i>-That's why Hyuk-joon's so meticulous.</i>
<i>-That's right.</i>

567
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:55,744
-I'm really nervous.
-Why?

568
00:24:56,536 --> 00:24:57,913
Shall we guess?

569
00:24:57,996 --> 00:24:59,456
-A news anchor.
-A news anchor.

570
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:00,707
It suits her.

571
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:03,501
-Maybe she's a dancer.
-That's right.

572
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:04,878
-A dancer.
-It suits her too.

573
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,171
Those are your guesses?

574
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:07,756
I'm…

575
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:12,260
a curator.

576
00:25:12,969 --> 00:25:14,012
-So cool!
-It suits you.

577
00:25:14,095 --> 00:25:15,513
It totally suits you.

578
00:25:16,806 --> 00:25:19,100
-A curator.
-That's why she's so well-spoken.

579
00:25:23,063 --> 00:25:27,567
<i>I'm currently working</i>
<i>as a curator at a gallery.</i>

580
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:28,485
<i>She totally looks it.</i>

581
00:25:28,568 --> 00:25:29,945
<i>I sell the artworks</i>

582
00:25:30,654 --> 00:25:34,032
<i>and discover new artists.</i>

583
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:37,744
<i>It has been four months</i>
<i>since I started my job.</i>

584
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:40,288
<i>I'm working as an intern.</i>

585
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:42,999
<i>-It fits her perfectly!</i>
-<i>She has that vibe.</i>

586
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:44,292
<i>She's made for that job.</i>

587
00:25:46,461 --> 00:25:47,754
Is it my turn?

588
00:25:48,505 --> 00:25:51,466
<i>I've always liked exhibitions.</i>
<i>I really do.</i>

589
00:25:51,549 --> 00:25:55,637
<i>I thought, "Gosh, this is incredible.</i>
<i>She's someone who introduces what I like."</i>

590
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:56,888
Is this fate?

591
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:59,099
I know I'm getting ahead of myself, but…

592
00:25:59,182 --> 00:26:01,935
<i>I thought we might be</i>
<i>meant for each other.</i>

593
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,730
He likes exhibitions? Give me a break!

594
00:26:06,773 --> 00:26:09,609
-Hyuk-joon likes everything about her.
-At this point…

595
00:26:09,693 --> 00:26:13,029
I know. He would've called it fate
even if her job was something else.

596
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:16,408
If she were a robber,
he would've gone, "I love robbing!"

597
00:26:16,491 --> 00:26:18,702
"You stole my heart,
so it makes sense that you're a robber."

598
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:21,871
SOO-HYUN

599
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:23,456
I'm a university student.

600
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:27,377
I major in Western painting
in the Art department.

601
00:26:28,503 --> 00:26:29,546
Art…

602
00:26:31,548 --> 00:26:33,717
<i>At Kyungpook National University,</i>

603
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:36,177
<i>I major in Western painting</i>
<i>in the Art department.</i>

604
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:42,017
<i>I'm focusing on media art,</i>
<i>which is my current main interest.</i>

605
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:42,976
KIM SOO-HYUN, ART STUDENT

606
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:44,477
<i>It suits her perfectly.</i>

607
00:26:45,228 --> 00:26:48,023
No wonder the splattered paint
looked so good on you earlier.

608
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:52,485
She's a natural.

609
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:54,529
The last one.

610
00:26:54,612 --> 00:26:56,197
Yes. Shall we guess?

611
00:26:56,781 --> 00:26:58,325
I bet you're a university student.

612
00:26:58,408 --> 00:27:00,327
Oh, really?

613
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:04,164
Maybe his job requires him to be eloquent.
You never know.

614
00:27:04,247 --> 00:27:06,583
Right, he might be
completely different when he works.

615
00:27:08,293 --> 00:27:09,252
I'm…

616
00:27:13,465 --> 00:27:14,466
I'm a dentist.

617
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:23,350
He's a doctor, a dentist.

618
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:25,143
I did not see that coming.

619
00:27:25,643 --> 00:27:26,728
Oh my!

620
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,396
I want to watch him at work.

621
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,106
-I can't imagine it.
-How unexpected.

622
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:32,400
<i>I'm a dentist.</i>

623
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:37,322
<i>After graduating</i>
<i>from Jeonbuk National University,</i>

624
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:40,200
<i>-I'm working as a public health doctor.</i>
<i>-A public health doctor.</i>

625
00:27:41,117 --> 00:27:43,870
<i>I go to places</i>
<i>such as senior community centers</i>

626
00:27:43,953 --> 00:27:47,582
<i>to give lectures</i>
<i>and provide dental checkups.</i>

627
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,752
<i>-It's completely unexpected.</i>
<i>-How cool.</i>

628
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:52,170
AHN SEUNG-HYUN, DENTIST

629
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:53,922
It was a surprise.

630
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:56,383
-I agree. The most unexpected.
-<i>Everyone is surprised.</i>

631
00:27:56,466 --> 00:27:59,677
-I thought he'd be a university student.
-Yeah, I thought so too.

632
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:04,766
<i>But he didn't seem like a dentist.</i>

633
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:07,268
<i>He seems to be really shy.</i>

634
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:09,896
<i>He appeared a bit clumsy and awkward too.</i>

635
00:28:09,979 --> 00:28:13,942
<i>He was incredibly shy and looked young,</i>

636
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:16,027
<i>so I was surprised to find out</i>
<i>that he is a dentist.</i>

637
00:28:16,861 --> 00:28:18,196
<i>I was very taken aback.</i>

638
00:28:18,279 --> 00:28:20,949
It wasn't what I expected.

639
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:23,660
He was actually a man of surprises.

640
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:25,286
A big surprise.

641
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:27,539
Maybe his professional side comes out
when he's working.

642
00:28:27,622 --> 00:28:29,290
<i>-Look at Hyuk-joon.</i>
<i>-Exactly.</i>

643
00:28:29,999 --> 00:28:34,421
I thought, "Oh, this could sway
Hyun-seo's heart."

644
00:28:35,004 --> 00:28:37,382
<i>Since I found his job cool too,</i>

645
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:40,969
<i>I thought Hyun-seo might prefer</i>
<i>a practitioner like a dentist</i>

646
00:28:41,052 --> 00:28:43,888
<i>over a marketer.</i>

647
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:46,683
<i>I thought she might be more drawn to him.</i>

648
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:50,979
Like Hyuk-joon said,

649
00:28:51,062 --> 00:28:54,274
will their feelings and choices change

650
00:28:54,357 --> 00:28:57,235
upon learning about each other's jobs?

651
00:28:57,318 --> 00:28:59,612
When you think about Season One…

652
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:01,948
I don't think they'll change.

653
00:29:02,031 --> 00:29:05,702
Right. But the participants of Season Two

654
00:29:05,785 --> 00:29:07,454
-are on the older side.
-Right.

655
00:29:07,537 --> 00:29:08,705
Some are in their thirties.

656
00:29:08,788 --> 00:29:12,292
At that age, jobs are kind of important
when you go on a blind date.

657
00:29:12,375 --> 00:29:13,877
It'd be strange not to care about it.

658
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:14,794
-I agree.
-Right.

659
00:29:14,878 --> 00:29:18,423
So I think the job reveal
could make them change their minds.

660
00:29:18,506 --> 00:29:21,301
-I think so too. Yes.
-Unlike Season One.

661
00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:24,637
Can we get a dental scaling
before we leave?

662
00:29:27,474 --> 00:29:28,808
<i>What does the text say?</i>

663
00:29:29,851 --> 00:29:31,686
Random Spot Date.

664
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:34,105
<i>-Here comes the Random Spot Date.</i>
<i>-Will they go on a date now?</i>

665
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:35,690
<i>They need to go on one in the evening.</i>

666
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:36,608
An envelope?

667
00:29:37,150 --> 00:29:38,943
Do we pick from here?

668
00:29:39,694 --> 00:29:40,862
Pick one each.

669
00:29:40,945 --> 00:29:41,821
Oh, do we pick one?

670
00:29:44,115 --> 00:29:47,202
<i>This time, they'll get to talk</i>
<i>to one person</i>

671
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:49,078
<i>they choose at random.</i>

672
00:29:49,162 --> 00:29:51,498
Romance often began
during the Random Spot Dates.

673
00:29:51,581 --> 00:29:53,708
That's right.
They were like, "Is this fate?"

674
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,001
Shall we go?

675
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:57,837
<i>Since the two of us can talk by ourselves,</i>

676
00:29:57,921 --> 00:29:59,756
the date will bring us closer.

677
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:02,884
I'll try to lead
the conversation a bit more.

678
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:05,845
It'll be nice to talk
and get to know the other person better.

679
00:30:05,929 --> 00:30:09,182
I thought if I get to talk to her
once more today,

680
00:30:09,265 --> 00:30:12,435
I might be able to lock in my chances.

681
00:30:16,731 --> 00:30:17,732
TIME LIMIT: 15 MINUTES

682
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,025
<i>Fifteen minutes.</i>

683
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:23,071
<i>This date is important.</i>

684
00:30:23,571 --> 00:30:25,782
LOUNGE

685
00:30:25,865 --> 00:30:27,408
This bug…

686
00:30:28,743 --> 00:30:31,204
-<i>Gosh, not again.</i>
-<i>He's so obsessed with bugs.</i>

687
00:30:32,413 --> 00:30:34,290
<i>While I was waiting,</i>

688
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:36,709
I hoped that Seo-yoon would come.

689
00:30:37,418 --> 00:30:38,962
-Of course.
-He's really loyal too.

690
00:30:39,045 --> 00:30:40,088
I know.

691
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:44,759
After you.

692
00:30:48,555 --> 00:30:50,056
-Guess who?
-Guess who?

693
00:30:50,139 --> 00:30:51,391
-What?
-Between the two of us…

694
00:30:51,474 --> 00:30:52,976
Is that why you came in together?

695
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:54,519
-Hello.
-Hi.

696
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:55,812
<i>It's Soo-hyun.</i>

697
00:30:55,895 --> 00:30:57,272
I got the Lounge.

698
00:30:58,231 --> 00:31:00,942
Soo-hyun's second pick was Jae-seo.

699
00:31:01,025 --> 00:31:02,068
Exactly.

700
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:04,070
<i>Soo-hyun came.</i>

701
00:31:04,153 --> 00:31:06,656
It was actually not so bad
that Soo-hyun came

702
00:31:06,739 --> 00:31:08,658
because she's Seo-yoon's roommate.

703
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:10,910
<i>I thought it'd be nice to talk to her.</i>

704
00:31:12,620 --> 00:31:15,248
<i>To be honest, the man</i>
<i>I wanted to get to know the most</i>

705
00:31:15,331 --> 00:31:16,666
was Jae-seo.

706
00:31:16,749 --> 00:31:19,794
<i>He was my second pick, after all.</i>

707
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:23,047
So I thought it'd be great
to talk to him today.

708
00:31:23,131 --> 00:31:24,257
I went, "Nice!"

709
00:31:24,757 --> 00:31:25,925
<i>I was happy.</i>

710
00:31:27,510 --> 00:31:30,346
-Isn't this our first conversation?
-The first one-on-one conversation.

711
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:32,974
I bet it's the same for almost everyone.

712
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:34,475
So,

713
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:37,353
-you must've gotten a sense of everyone.
-Right.

714
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:41,900
-As for the first impression vote…
-Yes.

715
00:31:41,983 --> 00:31:43,401
Who did you pick? Can I ask?

716
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:45,486
Well,

717
00:31:46,112 --> 00:31:47,947
I'll answer
only if we'll exchange information.

718
00:31:48,531 --> 00:31:51,242
It won't be fair
if you don't share your pick.

719
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:52,744
-You have a point.
-Yes.

720
00:31:54,078 --> 00:31:55,204
Then I'll go first.

721
00:31:56,164 --> 00:31:57,290
Well…

722
00:31:58,291 --> 00:32:00,668
I picked Seung-hyun.

723
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:02,337
He was my top pick.

724
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:03,713
It's an exchange. Tell me yours.

725
00:32:05,423 --> 00:32:06,591
Who did you pick?

726
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,386
Your roommate.

727
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:14,307
You had a date with her today.

728
00:32:14,390 --> 00:32:16,726
-We had a date, right?
-That's right.

729
00:32:16,809 --> 00:32:18,895
-We did partner dancing.
-Exactly.

730
00:32:18,978 --> 00:32:21,397
We held hands like this and…
You heard how it went, right?

731
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:23,024
-Yes.
-Exactly.

732
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:26,110
My brain was about to burst
because there was so much to process.

733
00:32:26,194 --> 00:32:28,529
"I shouldn't do this and that."

734
00:32:28,613 --> 00:32:30,949
Wait. I bet you were too nervous
to do anything.

735
00:32:31,032 --> 00:32:33,868
I got the rhythm wrong
for the dance moves I had memorized.

736
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:36,955
-I bet.
-I wasn't nervous at first.

737
00:32:37,038 --> 00:32:39,165
-It must've been nerve-racking.
-But we were standing close,

738
00:32:39,248 --> 00:32:40,708
so I became nervous.

739
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:42,293
So…

740
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:45,129
That was an issue.

741
00:32:45,213 --> 00:32:47,215
Is Seo-yoon your ideal type, looks-wise?

742
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:49,384
Yes.

743
00:32:50,677 --> 00:32:53,304
<i>He's telling her everything honestly.</i>

744
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:56,057
-You know, I was the first one to arrive.
-Okay.

745
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:57,642
I was sitting there by myself.

746
00:32:57,725 --> 00:33:00,269
When the second person opened the door,
I thought it was a scam.

747
00:33:00,353 --> 00:33:02,897
-Was she your dream girl looks-wise?
-Looks-wise, my dream girl

748
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,608
is Park Bo-young.
I like someone like that.

749
00:33:05,692 --> 00:33:06,985
Seo-yoon's got that vibe.

750
00:33:08,486 --> 00:33:11,197
I'm surprised at myself.
I never thought I'd be on this show.

751
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:15,702
<i>So many thoughts filled my head.</i>

752
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:19,163
Jae-seo was my second pick.

753
00:33:19,247 --> 00:33:21,040
But if he's so sure already…

754
00:33:21,124 --> 00:33:24,252
Also, he's interested in Seo-yoon,
and she's my roommate.

755
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:26,004
So that made me think

756
00:33:26,087 --> 00:33:28,589
I might end up being a third wheel.

757
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,342
So there was a lot going through my head.

758
00:33:31,426 --> 00:33:32,844
But well…

759
00:33:32,927 --> 00:33:36,097
Honestly, I can't share with you

760
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:37,890
what Seo-yoon tells me.

761
00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:39,100
-Of course not.
-Right.

762
00:33:39,726 --> 00:33:41,436
But I can still hear you out.

763
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,562
-Right.
-Yes.

764
00:33:43,354 --> 00:33:45,023
Suddenly, I feel…

765
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:47,483
I was so exhausted today.

766
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:49,861
-But I feel better now.
-I'm glad to hear that.

767
00:33:49,944 --> 00:33:52,655
I think it's nice.

768
00:33:53,406 --> 00:33:55,575
Soo-hyun, put it there. We're allies.

769
00:33:56,159 --> 00:33:56,993
We're allies.

770
00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:02,206
Still, he's her second pick.

771
00:34:02,290 --> 00:34:05,209
-Well, Jae-seo's clueless, so…
-Right.

772
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:09,297
-Things might change, but until then…
-Things can change.

773
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:10,673
Let's call it the E Union.

774
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:12,800
The E Union?
I see, "E" for extroverts. Right.

775
00:34:12,884 --> 00:34:14,719
Like the EU, the European Union.

776
00:34:15,845 --> 00:34:17,263
It's the EU.

777
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:20,058
<i>After talking to him…</i>

778
00:34:22,018 --> 00:34:24,645
Jae-seo's still my second pick.

779
00:34:24,729 --> 00:34:28,816
We had a conversation
even though it was a short one,

780
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,778
and I realized we had chemistry.

781
00:34:31,861 --> 00:34:34,322
That made me think

782
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:36,991
we'd be very compatible.

783
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:39,035
Oh, so she didn't have a change of heart.

784
00:34:39,118 --> 00:34:41,788
My feelings haven't changed
regarding Soo-hyun.

785
00:34:41,871 --> 00:34:43,581
The only change is

786
00:34:43,664 --> 00:34:47,085
that I'm more interested in Seo-yoon.

787
00:34:47,168 --> 00:34:49,796
I'm at a level
where she's constantly on my mind.

788
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:52,131
I want to know what she's up to.

789
00:34:52,215 --> 00:34:54,884
Before, it was,
"She seems like a nice person."

790
00:34:54,967 --> 00:34:57,637
Now, it's, "What is she up to?"

791
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:59,597
"Where is she?"

792
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:02,100
WHAT WOULD BE THE NEXT LEVEL?

793
00:35:02,683 --> 00:35:06,395
I guess it'd turn into a crush.

794
00:35:08,147 --> 00:35:10,566
His feelings for Seo-yoon grew deeper.

795
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:14,070
Jae-seo seems like a devoted man
who only has eyes for one person.

796
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:15,238
-I know.
-But

797
00:35:15,321 --> 00:35:18,157
-Jae-seo should voice his interest.
-That's right.

798
00:35:18,241 --> 00:35:21,035
-Talking to the camera won't help.
-That's right.

799
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:21,953
AGUNGI TEA ROOM

800
00:35:22,036 --> 00:35:23,955
-My goodness.
-<i>Agungi Tea Room?</i>

801
00:35:24,038 --> 00:35:25,248
It's decorated…

802
00:35:27,083 --> 00:35:28,668
in a Korean style.

803
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:34,298
Can we drink this?

804
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,512
<i>I thought it'd be nice</i>

805
00:35:39,595 --> 00:35:42,473
to talk to Hyun-seo some more.

806
00:35:42,557 --> 00:35:43,558
Who will it be?

807
00:35:44,183 --> 00:35:45,143
Who will come?

808
00:35:46,060 --> 00:35:49,105
<i>I could see three women</i>
<i>walking toward me from afar.</i>

809
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:51,649
Hyun-seo was one of them. I saw her.

810
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,193
But I was very nervous,

811
00:35:54,277 --> 00:35:55,611
<i>so I pretended I didn't see her.</i>

812
00:35:55,695 --> 00:35:58,447
<i>I kept my eyes straight ahead</i>
<i>and sat still, like a statue.</i>

813
00:36:00,324 --> 00:36:01,367
<i>Who is it?</i>

814
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:07,498
What?

815
00:36:08,082 --> 00:36:09,876
-Did you pick Agungi Tea Room?
-Yes.

816
00:36:10,835 --> 00:36:13,337
-We picked the same thing again?
-Seriously,

817
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:15,506
it's so fascinating. Are you serious?

818
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:16,799
Yes.

819
00:36:16,883 --> 00:36:17,967
What?

820
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:21,220
It's fate!

821
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:23,764
-Hyuk-joon must be over the moon.
-You know, Hyuk-joon

822
00:36:23,848 --> 00:36:25,349
won't change his mind after this.

823
00:36:25,433 --> 00:36:27,935
-They're set.
-I bet Hyuk-joon imagined their wedding.

824
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:30,396
-Probably even their grandkids.
-He must think it's totally fate.

825
00:36:30,479 --> 00:36:33,774
<i>It was unbelievable.</i>
<i>I got a serious dopamine rush.</i>

826
00:36:34,901 --> 00:36:38,738
My dopamine levels were
going through the roof.

827
00:36:38,821 --> 00:36:41,407
<i>It was giving me goosebumps.</i>

828
00:36:41,490 --> 00:36:44,452
<i>That's how I was feeling.</i>

829
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:48,706
Also, Hyun-seo was
the last to pick an envelope.

830
00:36:48,789 --> 00:36:52,126
<i>I thought she wanted to talk</i>
<i>to someone else.</i>

831
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:55,504
So seeing her gave me goosebumps all over.

832
00:36:56,422 --> 00:36:58,007
<i>I was so happy.</i>

833
00:36:58,090 --> 00:36:59,425
Even I got goosebumps too.

834
00:37:00,134 --> 00:37:02,345
It's unbelievable. What the heck?

835
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:06,682
-By the way,
-Yes?

836
00:37:06,766 --> 00:37:09,060
was there anyone you wanted to talk to?

837
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:12,563
To be completely honest,

838
00:37:12,647 --> 00:37:14,941
I picked you
for the first impression vote.

839
00:37:15,524 --> 00:37:18,402
-Really?
-So I wanted to talk to you.

840
00:37:19,028 --> 00:37:22,448
And I had so much fun today

841
00:37:22,531 --> 00:37:25,117
doing an activity with you.

842
00:37:25,201 --> 00:37:26,869
-Really?
-Yes.

843
00:37:26,953 --> 00:37:29,705
You were so good at the game today.

844
00:37:29,789 --> 00:37:32,333
-I was a bit worried
-Okay.

845
00:37:32,416 --> 00:37:34,752
because I walked around
with a gun like this.

846
00:37:34,835 --> 00:37:36,796
"What will he think
about the way I opened fire?"

847
00:37:36,879 --> 00:37:38,339
I was a bit worried.

848
00:37:38,422 --> 00:37:40,216
You did? But I thought…

849
00:37:41,342 --> 00:37:43,844
-I found you really cool.
-Really?

850
00:37:46,722 --> 00:37:47,765
By the way…

851
00:37:47,848 --> 00:37:50,935
I'm curious too. Is there anyone
you want to go on a date with?

852
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:53,437
-There were two.
-Okay.

853
00:37:55,314 --> 00:37:56,315
And I had a date with both.

854
00:37:57,108 --> 00:37:58,025
Yes.

855
00:37:58,609 --> 00:37:59,902
I was very lucky.

856
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:02,446
That means Hyuk-joon was one of them.

857
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:05,116
-She kept it nicely vague.
-She did.

858
00:38:06,492 --> 00:38:08,369
-Then… I see.
-Yes.

859
00:38:08,452 --> 00:38:10,246
-Right, I see.
-Yes.

860
00:38:10,329 --> 00:38:11,289
So I was like,

861
00:38:12,164 --> 00:38:13,874
"I'm so lucky!"

862
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:17,670
I felt so lucky.

863
00:38:20,214 --> 00:38:23,884
<i>I told Hyun-seo that she was my pick</i>
<i>for the first impression vote.</i>

864
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:27,430
And she said she had two people in mind

865
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:28,556
and I was one of them.

866
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:30,308
When she told me that

867
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:33,102
in a roundabout way,

868
00:38:33,185 --> 00:38:35,730
<i>happiness was all I felt.</i>

869
00:38:35,813 --> 00:38:37,189
<i>Pure bliss.</i>

870
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:43,321
-Then…
-Yes?

871
00:38:43,404 --> 00:38:46,449
there must be someone else

872
00:38:46,532 --> 00:38:47,867
you want to talk to.

873
00:38:47,950 --> 00:38:49,744
-Someone I want to talk to?
-Yes.

874
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:56,500
-To be completely honest…
-Okay.

875
00:38:57,793 --> 00:38:58,836
There was no one else.

876
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:01,672
-Really?
-Yes.

877
00:39:01,756 --> 00:39:04,842
Perhaps I'm being too straightforward.

878
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:10,556
I absolutely love your voice.

879
00:39:11,932 --> 00:39:13,017
So…

880
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:15,895
Men usually don't like my voice.

881
00:39:16,479 --> 00:39:17,980
-You're wrong.
-It's low-pitched.

882
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:18,939
No.

883
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:20,024
-Really?
-Yes.

884
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:23,736
You know, there was something
I found fascinating.

885
00:39:23,819 --> 00:39:27,406
Apparently, my parents talked about
where to meet for their first date

886
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:30,826
-over the phone.
-Okay.

887
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:33,579
I asked my dad, and he said

888
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:37,291
that he fell for my mom's voice.

889
00:39:38,167 --> 00:39:39,126
So…

890
00:39:39,794 --> 00:39:42,755
I had forgotten that story,
but when I heard your voice,

891
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:44,882
I found it so charming.

892
00:39:44,965 --> 00:39:47,510
That's so fascinating.
No one has told me that before.

893
00:39:47,593 --> 00:39:50,262
You know, parents would ask you,

894
00:39:50,346 --> 00:39:54,392
"What kind of person
do you want to date and marry?"

895
00:39:54,475 --> 00:39:56,310
I said, "Someone like Mom."

896
00:39:57,019 --> 00:39:59,688
-Really?
-"I want to marry someone like Mom."

897
00:39:59,772 --> 00:40:01,982
This is unbelievable. Seriously.

898
00:40:04,193 --> 00:40:05,152
That's how I felt.

899
00:40:05,236 --> 00:40:06,779
It's my first time hearing

900
00:40:06,862 --> 00:40:10,449
-such a big compliment on my voice.
-Oh, really?

901
00:40:10,533 --> 00:40:12,910
Back in school,

902
00:40:12,993 --> 00:40:14,995
my voice was even more low-pitched.

903
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:18,958
So, my friends said
that I sounded like a man

904
00:40:19,458 --> 00:40:21,961
and made fun of me.

905
00:40:22,044 --> 00:40:24,672
That made me very self-conscious
about my voice.

906
00:40:24,755 --> 00:40:25,756
Really?

907
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,675
But I think it's so charming.

908
00:40:28,217 --> 00:40:29,176
Thanks.

909
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:34,140
Do you believe in fate?

910
00:40:34,849 --> 00:40:36,600
-Yes, I do.
-You do?

911
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:39,186
They say repeated coincidences mean fate.

912
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,813
That's right.

913
00:40:40,896 --> 00:40:41,730
But…

914
00:40:43,023 --> 00:40:45,192
-this feels like fate.
-Fate?

915
00:40:46,485 --> 00:40:47,862
To be honest,

916
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:50,406
I placed second in arm-wrestling
on purpose today.

917
00:40:51,198 --> 00:40:53,701
But it's a pure coincidence

918
00:40:53,784 --> 00:40:56,245
that you got me for this date.

919
00:40:57,329 --> 00:40:58,956
<i>Hyuk-joon said</i>

920
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:02,042
that repeated coincidences mean fate.

921
00:41:02,543 --> 00:41:06,172
So I thought, "That might be the case."

922
00:41:07,339 --> 00:41:10,676
<i>And he told me that I have a nice voice.</i>

923
00:41:10,759 --> 00:41:12,928
I've been self-conscious

924
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:16,348
about my voice for many years,

925
00:41:16,432 --> 00:41:19,393
so I never thought
that I had a nice voice.

926
00:41:19,477 --> 00:41:22,605
So his words meant a lot to me.

927
00:41:23,898 --> 00:41:27,359
During the Random Spot Date,

928
00:41:27,443 --> 00:41:30,821
Hyuk-joon totally became my top pick.

929
00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:32,281
-Okay.
-Of course.

930
00:41:32,364 --> 00:41:33,574
-He became her top pick.
-Good.

931
00:41:33,657 --> 00:41:36,243
-She said, "Totally."
-Hyuk-joon made it.

932
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:38,120
I was worried he was coming on too strong.

933
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:40,664
In Season One,
we had a participant who said,

934
00:41:40,748 --> 00:41:43,125
"I'd like a daughter like you."

935
00:41:43,209 --> 00:41:44,251
That's right.

936
00:41:44,335 --> 00:41:46,921
And in Season Two, we have a participant
talking about his mom.

937
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:50,591
Talking about the parents that early
means it's game over.

938
00:41:50,674 --> 00:41:51,592
Now, just go for it.

939
00:41:51,675 --> 00:41:53,469
-Go.
-The two of them will go for it.

940
00:41:53,552 --> 00:41:55,179
<i>This isn't the place!</i>

941
00:41:55,262 --> 00:41:56,305
<i>Where is it?</i>

942
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:58,516
<i>-It must be the place from earlier.</i>
<i>-Where is it?</i>

943
00:41:58,599 --> 00:41:59,642
Where?

944
00:42:00,976 --> 00:42:01,810
<i>-Su-ji.</i>
<i>-It's Su-ji.</i>

945
00:42:02,394 --> 00:42:03,437
It's here.

946
00:42:05,898 --> 00:42:06,815
I'm such a fool.

947
00:42:08,317 --> 00:42:12,112
<i>The ones I wanted were</i>
<i>Seung-hyun and Jung-yun.</i>

948
00:42:12,196 --> 00:42:15,115
During our date, Seung-hyun and I
only danced and did nothing else.

949
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:17,576
<i>So we became close very quickly,</i>

950
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:20,871
<i>but we didn't really have</i>
<i>the time to talk,</i>

951
00:42:20,955 --> 00:42:21,997
<i>which was a shame.</i>

952
00:42:22,081 --> 00:42:24,458
<i>As for Jung-yun…</i>

953
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:26,710
<i>I haven't had a chance</i>
<i>to talk to him at all.</i>

954
00:42:27,711 --> 00:42:31,966
<i>So I wanted to talk</i>
<i>to either Seung-hyun or Jung-yun.</i>

955
00:42:32,049 --> 00:42:34,218
But it was a random date
at the end of the day,

956
00:42:34,301 --> 00:42:36,804
so I left it up to fate.

957
00:42:44,979 --> 00:42:46,272
-Hi.
-Hey.

958
00:42:47,523 --> 00:42:48,691
<i>-It's Seung-hyun.</i>
<i>-Seung-hyun.</i>

959
00:42:48,774 --> 00:42:49,775
-Hi.
-<i>It's Seung-hyun.</i>

960
00:42:49,858 --> 00:42:51,193
Did you pick this place too?

961
00:42:52,152 --> 00:42:54,280
-Come have a seat here.
-It's my first time here.

962
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:57,032
-I think it'll be warm over there.
-Shall we go over there?

963
00:42:57,616 --> 00:42:59,493
<i>I'm glad she got the person she wanted.</i>

964
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:01,495
<i>I got paired up with Seung-hyun.</i>

965
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:03,497
I was very surprised

966
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:05,541
to see him at the top of the staircase.

967
00:43:05,624 --> 00:43:06,709
So I went, "What?"

968
00:43:07,293 --> 00:43:08,419
So you picked this place.

969
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:11,755
I picked this place
because I'd never been here.

970
00:43:12,339 --> 00:43:13,424
Is it your first time here?

971
00:43:13,507 --> 00:43:14,883
-Yes, it is.
-Do you want a blanket?

972
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,719
-It's okay.
-Really? Aren't you cold?

973
00:43:16,802 --> 00:43:19,054
-You look so uncomfortable.
-I am, but…

974
00:43:19,138 --> 00:43:20,723
-I'll do this.
-What's that on the floor?

975
00:43:20,806 --> 00:43:22,683
It's a foot bath.

976
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:24,810
They won't use the foot bath.

977
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:27,855
-Don't bother giving them baths or tubs.
-Like a pool?

978
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:29,690
-They won't use them.
-They won't go in.

979
00:43:29,773 --> 00:43:31,609
Shall we move to the side?

980
