<i>Oh, they're here.</i>

1221
00:52:52,669 --> 00:52:54,421
-Welcome back.
-Hey.

1222
00:52:54,504 --> 00:52:56,423
We were talking
about the changes in our picks.

1223
00:52:57,465 --> 00:52:59,968
-I told you about my picks yesterday.
-Yes.

1224
00:53:00,051 --> 00:53:02,387
They've changed today.

1225
00:53:02,470 --> 00:53:03,513
We were talking about that.

1226
00:53:03,597 --> 00:53:08,101
Now, my top pick is Seung-hyun,
and my second pick is Jung-yun.

1227
00:53:08,184 --> 00:53:11,354
Jung-yun is my second pick
because I haven't talked to him yet.

1228
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:13,690
If I talk to him
and get along better with him,

1229
00:53:13,773 --> 00:53:16,401
then I might have a change of heart.

1230
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:18,528
How about you all? Any change of heart?

1231
00:53:19,070 --> 00:53:20,906
-Yes.
-Like what?

1232
00:53:20,989 --> 00:53:22,490
-I…
-Who was your top pick?

1233
00:53:22,574 --> 00:53:26,828
Looks-wise, the one
who was closest to my ideal type

1234
00:53:26,912 --> 00:53:27,996
was Jung-yun.

1235
00:53:28,788 --> 00:53:30,415
So, Jung-yun was my top pick.

1236
00:53:30,498 --> 00:53:34,169
Our conversations went very well,

1237
00:53:34,252 --> 00:53:36,171
without any awkward pauses.

1238
00:53:36,254 --> 00:53:38,506
When I'd ask him something,

1239
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:40,508
-he made sure
-He put in a lot of effort?

1240
00:53:40,592 --> 00:53:42,719
to give me answers
he put in some thought into.

1241
00:53:44,971 --> 00:53:48,099
As for me, my top pick is Jin-woo,
and my second pick is…

1242
00:53:48,183 --> 00:53:50,185
I'm not sure about my second pick.

1243
00:53:50,268 --> 00:53:53,563
I'm not sure if I'm attracted to him
or I just find him fun to be around.

1244
00:53:55,315 --> 00:53:57,067
-You guys need to talk more.
-Exactly.

1245
00:53:57,859 --> 00:53:59,110
I have a question.

1246
00:53:59,194 --> 00:54:04,074
Jin-woo is my second pick,
and I also have a bit of interest in him.

1247
00:54:04,157 --> 00:54:06,076
Is his height okay to you?

1248
00:54:06,159 --> 00:54:07,619
-Well…
-You're quite tall too.

1249
00:54:07,702 --> 00:54:09,287
-Soo-hyun is tall.
-She's tall.

1250
00:54:09,371 --> 00:54:11,039
She's over 170 cm tall.

1251
00:54:11,122 --> 00:54:14,542
-Well, I gave it some serious thought.
-Right.

1252
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:17,128
After all, when asked about my ideal type,

1253
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,381
height would always be
at the top of my list.

1254
00:54:19,464 --> 00:54:23,551
I'd always say, "I want a man
who's taller than me."

1255
00:54:23,635 --> 00:54:26,012
But Jin-woo's height doesn't bother me.

1256
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:27,764
-You don't find it bothering.
-No.

1257
00:54:28,390 --> 00:54:30,100
Doesn't that mean she likes him a lot?

1258
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:32,227
-I guess you guys got along well.
-Yes.

1259
00:54:32,310 --> 00:54:33,895
During the paintball date,

1260
00:54:33,979 --> 00:54:36,231
I didn't think about his height at all.

1261
00:54:36,314 --> 00:54:40,694
Well, he's a man with good manners.

1262
00:54:41,194 --> 00:54:43,196
For now, he's my top pick.

1263
00:54:44,990 --> 00:54:47,951
I said Jin-woo looked like Lai Kuan-lin.

1264
00:54:48,034 --> 00:54:50,203
-Lai Kuan-lin?
-He could pass as his twin.

1265
00:54:50,286 --> 00:54:51,371
-No.
-No, he can't.

1266
00:54:51,454 --> 00:54:53,748
-So when he entered, I thought…
-What are you on about?

1267
00:54:53,832 --> 00:54:55,834
I guess we're blinded by love!

1268
00:54:55,917 --> 00:54:57,544
I guess he's their type.

1269
00:54:57,627 --> 00:55:00,922
When he first showed up,
I thought his face is totally my type.

1270
00:55:01,006 --> 00:55:02,590
-Really? Seriously?
-Yes.

1271
00:55:02,674 --> 00:55:05,635
I still haven't had a chance
to talk to him.

1272
00:55:06,553 --> 00:55:08,888
But I can't completely
look past his height.

1273
00:55:08,972 --> 00:55:11,141
I was curious
since you're even taller than me.

1274
00:55:11,224 --> 00:55:14,060
Well, you might change your mind
once you get to talk to him.

1275
00:55:14,144 --> 00:55:17,814
His height didn't bother me at all.

1276
00:55:19,482 --> 00:55:20,650
But this is too…

1277
00:55:20,734 --> 00:55:22,402
-They're oversharing.
-It's only day two…

1278
00:55:22,485 --> 00:55:24,279
Is it okay to lay it all out there

1279
00:55:24,362 --> 00:55:25,822
-on day two?
-I know. Exactly.

1280
00:55:25,905 --> 00:55:26,948
Let's come up with a rule.

1281
00:55:27,032 --> 00:55:30,660
It should be, "Don't lay
all of your cards on the table."

1282
00:55:30,744 --> 00:55:34,080
I had fun listening to them talk,
but I don't know if that's okay.

1283
00:55:34,164 --> 00:55:35,373
People don't usually do that.

1284
00:55:35,457 --> 00:55:37,709
But they don't know that
since they're eternal singles.

1285
00:55:42,297 --> 00:55:43,298
<i>Did you sleep well?</i>

1286
00:55:43,381 --> 00:55:44,340
<i>I slept well.</i>

1287
00:55:44,424 --> 00:55:46,384
<i>-I woke up at 6 a.m.</i>
<i>-Oh, yeah?</i>

1288
00:55:46,468 --> 00:55:47,969
Thank goodness it's not raining.

1289
00:55:48,053 --> 00:55:48,887
Yeah.

1290
00:55:48,970 --> 00:55:50,764
-There's no rain forecast.
-No.

1291
00:55:52,390 --> 00:55:53,349
Hold on.

1292
00:55:57,937 --> 00:56:00,315
I want to play it. I'm curious.

1293
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:01,775
I want to go play it.

1294
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:03,359
Play what?

1295
00:56:04,235 --> 00:56:06,154
<i>I enjoy playing the piano.</i>

1296
00:56:06,237 --> 00:56:08,073
<i>It's something I do for fun.</i>

1297
00:56:08,156 --> 00:56:11,326
-He'll be less shy with no girls around.
-That's right.

1298
00:56:11,409 --> 00:56:12,577
We'll get a front-row view.

1299
00:56:12,660 --> 00:56:13,870
Turn toward him.

1300
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:16,664
He should play it
when the girls are around.

1301
00:56:22,337 --> 00:56:25,006
-That's cheating.
-"That's cheating."

1302
00:56:25,090 --> 00:56:27,383
-Jung-yun, why play it now?
-Jung-yun, why now…

1303
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:29,135
That's enough. Stop now.

1304
00:56:41,272 --> 00:56:43,900
If he played the piano around girls,
he'd win major points.

1305
00:56:43,983 --> 00:56:44,818
Exactly.

1306
00:56:44,901 --> 00:56:47,112
-That's cheating. Get rid of the piano.
-That's cheating.

1307
00:56:47,195 --> 00:56:48,905
It shouldn't count.

1308
00:56:48,988 --> 00:56:51,032
If you see an axe
through it tomorrow, it'd be my doing.

1309
00:56:51,741 --> 00:56:53,034
We need to break it.

1310
00:56:53,118 --> 00:56:55,120
-It's so cool.
-I know. So charming.

1311
00:56:56,121 --> 00:56:57,539
They're all sitting inside.

1312
00:56:59,707 --> 00:57:01,960
What? A secret performance?
Hurry up and play some more.

1313
00:57:02,627 --> 00:57:04,003
I'm so bad, though.

1314
00:57:06,131 --> 00:57:07,590
When did you learn how to play it?

1315
00:57:07,674 --> 00:57:09,008
I learned it in elementary school

1316
00:57:09,092 --> 00:57:11,010
and kept it up as a hobby
since I have a piano at home.

1317
00:57:11,678 --> 00:57:13,096
Why were you hanging out here?

1318
00:57:13,179 --> 00:57:15,014
I figured everyone would be here.

1319
00:57:15,098 --> 00:57:17,851
-It's too early for the Post Office.
-True.

1320
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,519
There wouldn't be anything.

1321
00:57:20,103 --> 00:57:21,396
<i>Let's check out the Post Office.</i>

1322
00:57:21,479 --> 00:57:22,856
<i>-It's right out front.</i>
<i>-Good.</i>

1323
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:23,857
ETERNAL SINGLES' POST OFFICE

1324
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,526
-Let's go to the Post Office.
-Post Office.

1325
00:57:27,652 --> 00:57:29,696
Shall I check my cabinet?

1326
00:57:30,363 --> 00:57:31,823
-Is there something?
-No.

1327
00:57:31,906 --> 00:57:32,782
I bet mine is empty too.

1328
00:57:34,576 --> 00:57:36,035
-Is there something?
-No.

1329
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:37,162
<i>It was empty.</i>

1330
00:57:37,245 --> 00:57:38,288
There was nothing,

1331
00:57:38,371 --> 00:57:41,374
so I figured everyone's still deciding.
And I closed the cabinet and left.

1332
00:57:41,458 --> 00:57:44,711
<i>I'm thinking about using</i>
<i>the Post Office now.</i>

1333
00:57:44,794 --> 00:57:48,381
<i>Each person can buy up to three gifts.</i>

1334
00:57:48,465 --> 00:57:51,468
I want to use my Gift Coupons wisely,

1335
00:57:51,551 --> 00:57:52,802
<i>so I'm saving them up for now.</i>

1336
00:57:52,886 --> 00:57:54,304
What do you mean, "save"?

1337
00:57:54,387 --> 00:57:55,346
Shall I open it?

1338
00:57:55,930 --> 00:57:56,931
Of course, it's empty.

1339
00:57:57,974 --> 00:57:59,684
<i>I opened it just in case.</i>

1340
00:57:59,767 --> 00:58:02,020
<i>But it was empty,</i>
<i>so I closed it and came back out.</i>

1341
00:58:02,103 --> 00:58:06,024
<i>I saw the writing paper and thought</i>
<i>I should write a letter soon.</i>

1342
00:58:07,442 --> 00:58:09,694
<i>I've always wanted to wear</i>

1343
00:58:09,777 --> 00:58:12,280
<i>matching bracelets with my girlfriend,</i>

1344
00:58:12,363 --> 00:58:14,741
<i>so I wanted to get bracelets that I liked.</i>

1345
00:58:14,824 --> 00:58:19,621
I'll give one to someone
and see if she wears it.

1346
00:58:26,419 --> 00:58:29,839
<i>I was really torn about</i>
<i>whether to use it today or not.</i>

1347
00:58:29,923 --> 00:58:30,840
A rose…

1348
00:58:30,924 --> 00:58:35,386
<i>I thought I might be able to use</i>
<i>the Gift Coupons if I got a chance.</i>

1349
00:58:36,387 --> 00:58:40,141
Everyone seems very torn.

1350
00:58:46,564 --> 00:58:48,066
<i>Someone gave her a gift!</i>

1351
00:58:48,983 --> 00:58:50,068
What?

1352
00:58:51,986 --> 00:58:53,071
Already?

1353
00:58:54,948 --> 00:58:56,157
What could it be?

1354
00:58:56,241 --> 00:58:57,575
If it's a perfume, it's from Hyuk-joon.

1355
00:59:00,870 --> 00:59:01,746
What is it?

1356
00:59:02,747 --> 00:59:05,041
<i>There were a letter and a tumbler.</i>

1357
00:59:06,042 --> 00:59:08,836
"Hello, Hyun-seo. It's very cold, right?"

1358
00:59:08,920 --> 00:59:11,089
"Drink warm water in your room."

1359
00:59:11,172 --> 00:59:14,676
"I got you a practical gift.
I hope you'll like it."

1360
00:59:15,385 --> 00:59:16,427
Oh my.

1361
00:59:17,345 --> 00:59:18,221
This is incredible.

1362
00:59:20,390 --> 00:59:21,307
Who is it from?

1363
00:59:22,392 --> 00:59:25,436
<i>I had no idea who it could be from.</i>
<i>I was totally clueless.</i>

1364
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:30,567
I wondered if it was Seung-hyun
because he saw how cold I was yesterday.

1365
00:59:31,150 --> 00:59:34,153
<i>Is that why the letter read,</i>
<i>"It's very cold, right?"</i>

1366
00:59:34,654 --> 00:59:36,155
It's cute.

1367
00:59:36,781 --> 00:59:37,949
Very cute.

1368
00:59:39,158 --> 00:59:42,036
It's pretty. It's my favorite color.

1369
00:59:42,870 --> 00:59:45,164
-Who gave it to her? Hyuk-joon?
-Who is it?

1370
00:59:45,248 --> 00:59:47,542
It's not a perfume,
so I doubt it's from Hyuk-joon.

1371
00:59:47,625 --> 00:59:49,377
That gift is very practical.

1372
00:59:49,460 --> 00:59:52,005
But Hyuk-joon would give
something more sentimental.

1373
00:59:52,505 --> 00:59:53,840
Is it from Seung-hyun?

1374
00:59:57,844 --> 00:59:58,720
<i>Huh, what?</i>

1375
00:59:59,304 --> 01:00:00,388
My phone!

1376
01:00:00,471 --> 01:00:02,515
"In 5 minutes…" 5 Minute Library?

1377
01:00:02,599 --> 01:00:04,892
The Library will open.

1378
01:00:04,976 --> 01:00:07,228
We need to go to the Eternal Singles' Hill
and ring the bell.

1379
01:00:07,312 --> 01:00:08,646
-What?
-First three people.

1380
01:00:08,730 --> 01:00:10,023
ETERNAL SINGLES' HILL

1381
01:00:10,106 --> 01:00:11,107
<i>Nice.</i>

1382
01:00:11,190 --> 01:00:13,443
ONLY THE FIRST THREE TO RING THE BELL
ON THE ETERNAL SINGLES' HILL CAN ENTER

1383
01:00:13,526 --> 01:00:15,737
It's a good chance
to gain information on their crush.

1384
01:00:15,820 --> 01:00:16,988
An excellent chance.

1385
01:00:17,071 --> 01:00:20,450
GO TO THE ETERNAL SINGLES' HILL
AND RING THE BELL NOW

1386
01:00:20,533 --> 01:00:22,035
Where is the Eternal Singles' Hill?

1387
01:00:22,118 --> 01:00:23,411
-Where is it?
-Where?

1388
01:00:23,494 --> 01:00:25,580
Where is it?

1389
01:00:26,080 --> 01:00:28,875
There are already three people
in front of me.

1390
01:00:28,958 --> 01:00:31,085
-Move!
-Hey, run!

1391
01:00:31,169 --> 01:00:33,338
Where? Where to?

1392
01:00:33,421 --> 01:00:34,464
-Hill?
-Isn't it that way?

1393
01:00:34,547 --> 01:00:35,465
Over there, no?

1394
01:00:35,548 --> 01:00:36,799
-No!
-<i>Run!</i>

1395
01:00:36,883 --> 01:00:38,301
<i>I had to run fast.</i>

1396
01:00:38,384 --> 01:00:39,969
<i>I ran up the hill like crazy.</i>

1397
01:00:40,053 --> 01:00:42,013
<i>I knew whose information</i>
<i>I wanted to check.</i>

1398
01:00:42,096 --> 01:00:44,140
<i>I was determined to check his.</i>

1399
01:00:44,223 --> 01:00:46,142
<i>"I'll run as fast as I can</i>

1400
01:00:46,225 --> 01:00:49,228
<i>and become the first to enjoy</i>
<i>the 5 Minute Library."</i>

1401
01:00:49,312 --> 01:00:51,022
<i>That's what was on my mind.</i>

1402
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:53,024
<i>Yes, Su-ji!</i>

1403
01:00:55,443 --> 01:00:57,403
-It's the jacuzzi from yesterday!
-That's the place!

1404
01:00:57,487 --> 01:00:58,321
Hurry up!

1405
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,075
Hold on. Wait…

1406
01:01:02,158 --> 01:01:03,534
<i>Just run!</i>

1407
01:01:03,618 --> 01:01:04,786
They're sprinting like that?

1408
01:01:05,370 --> 01:01:07,622
<i>I knew I should go fast.</i>

1409
01:01:07,705 --> 01:01:11,000
<i>Su-ji was wearing red,</i>

1410
01:01:11,084 --> 01:01:13,086
<i>and it was like a fire truck</i>
<i>was speeding by me.</i>

1411
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:15,296
<i>I thought I should stay out of it.</i>

1412
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:16,923
<i>I was a bit dazed.</i>

1413
01:01:18,383 --> 01:01:19,634
No!

1414
01:01:20,385 --> 01:01:21,219
No…

1415
01:01:22,845 --> 01:01:25,431
<i>Well done, Su-ji. Nice one.</i>

1416
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:26,599
First place.

1417
01:01:27,225 --> 01:01:29,310
<i>-Hyun-seo.</i>
<i>-Hyun-seo.</i>

1418
01:01:29,394 --> 01:01:30,269
SECOND PLACE, HYUN-SEO

1419
01:01:30,353 --> 01:01:32,563
-Why isn't it working?
-<i>Third place, Soo-hyun.</i>

1420
01:01:32,647 --> 01:01:34,232
It's all women?

1421
01:01:34,315 --> 01:01:37,318
-What on earth are the guys doing?
-What are the men doing?

1422
01:01:39,404 --> 01:01:41,155
What should I do about these flies?

1423
01:01:45,952 --> 01:01:47,829
I wish I had a fly swatter.

1424
01:01:47,912 --> 01:01:49,664
Are you a pest control service or what?

1425
01:01:50,373 --> 01:01:51,416
Jeez.

1426
01:01:51,499 --> 01:01:54,502
-Do something about him!
-I mean, Jae-seo…

1427
01:01:54,585 --> 01:01:56,337
-Jae-seo…
-Seriously.

1428
01:01:56,421 --> 01:01:59,382
-Is he from a pest control service?
-Let me say this.

1429
01:01:59,465 --> 01:02:01,050
-What's wrong with him?
-All he does is catch flies.

1430
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:04,178
Hear me out. Kim Jae-seo, just go home.

1431
01:02:05,138 --> 01:02:06,305
You…

1432
01:02:06,389 --> 01:02:07,515
You should just go home.

1433
01:02:07,598 --> 01:02:09,517
Jae-seo, you're out.

1434
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:10,560
-I mean…
-Jaest Control!

1435
01:02:11,269 --> 01:02:12,270
"Jaest Control."

1436
01:02:12,353 --> 01:02:13,855
That's a bit too…

1437
01:02:13,938 --> 01:02:15,732
-I mean…
-I'll be honest with you.

1438
01:02:15,815 --> 01:02:18,025
When he was getting
obsessed with the bugs,

1439
01:02:18,109 --> 01:02:19,902
I thought he was doing that

1440
01:02:19,986 --> 01:02:21,696
-because he was shy.
-Me too.

1441
01:02:21,779 --> 01:02:24,574
-But I was wrong. He's just Jaest Control.
-He's serious.

1442
01:02:24,657 --> 01:02:26,367
-He's obsessed with the flies.
-Seriously.

1443
01:02:27,577 --> 01:02:29,370
<i>These flies are reproducing so quickly.</i>

1444
01:02:29,454 --> 01:02:30,997
<i>I guess they aren't eternal singles.</i>

1445
01:02:33,875 --> 01:02:36,878
<i>He's acting like an employee</i>
<i>from a pest control service.</i>

1446
01:02:37,462 --> 01:02:39,839
-The hill is up very high, right?
-Yeah.

1447
01:02:40,631 --> 01:02:42,049
You'll trip if you aren't careful.

1448
01:02:42,633 --> 01:02:46,679
<i>The idea of racing there together</i>
<i>made me a bit uneasy.</i>

1449
01:02:46,763 --> 01:02:49,515
<i>So I let the others take the chance.</i>

1450
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:52,435
<i>I thought I wouldn't be able</i>
<i>to win the race,</i>

1451
01:02:52,518 --> 01:02:54,020
<i>so I didn't go.</i>

1452
01:02:54,103 --> 01:02:56,439
Everyone's glued to their seats. Great.

1453
01:02:56,522 --> 01:02:58,191
<i>"Great"?</i>

1454
01:02:58,775 --> 01:03:01,277
Seriously, that's lousy.

1455
01:03:01,360 --> 01:03:02,236
It really is.

1456
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:05,364
Let's say there are people
you're interested in.

1457
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:08,367
So you sprinted up the hill,
but they're glued to their seats.

1458
01:03:08,993 --> 01:03:10,161
-That's…
-You'd be let down.

1459
01:03:10,244 --> 01:03:13,039
-You'd feel like the only one invested.
-Seriously.

1460
01:03:13,122 --> 01:03:14,582
People could find you attractive

1461
01:03:14,665 --> 01:03:16,626
-if you sprint up the hill.
-I know.

1462
01:03:16,709 --> 01:03:19,128
Overall, the male participants
of this season

1463
01:03:19,212 --> 01:03:21,464
are very concerning.

1464
01:03:21,547 --> 01:03:22,381
Seriously.

1465
01:03:22,965 --> 01:03:26,636
PLEASE USE THE 5 MINUTE LIBRARY
IN THE ORDER YOU OBTAINED THE KEYS

1466
01:03:26,719 --> 01:03:28,179
I'm going in.

1467
01:03:32,475 --> 01:03:35,019
You can gain a lot of information here.

1468
01:03:35,102 --> 01:03:36,312
-That's right.
-Yes.

1469
01:03:36,896 --> 01:03:40,483
A LIBRARY WITH THE ETERNAL SINGLES'
HONEST ANSWERS TO 130 QUESTIONS

1470
01:03:46,739 --> 01:03:48,157
<i>Who will Su-ji pick?</i>

1471
01:03:48,991 --> 01:03:49,909
Five minutes.

1472
01:03:50,660 --> 01:03:53,412
<i>I was torn between two people.</i>

1473
01:03:53,913 --> 01:03:55,581
<i>One was Jung-yun,</i>

1474
01:03:55,665 --> 01:03:58,000
<i>and the other was Seung-hyun.</i>

1475
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:03,130
<i>Suddenly, the timer set off.</i>

1476
01:04:03,214 --> 01:04:04,340
Clock's ticking.

1477
01:04:06,092 --> 01:04:08,177
<i>I just grabbed</i>

1478
01:04:08,261 --> 01:04:10,930
<i>Jung-yun's diary without thinking.</i>

1479
01:04:11,973 --> 01:04:15,685
<i>I've talked to Seung-hyun</i>
<i>and gone on a date with him.</i>

1480
01:04:15,768 --> 01:04:19,564
But I'd had no interaction
with Jung-yun at all.

1481
01:04:19,647 --> 01:04:23,067
<i>So I was determined</i>
<i>to gain information about him with this.</i>

1482
01:04:23,693 --> 01:04:26,696
-The tangerine hat incident was big too.
-That's right.

1483
01:04:26,779 --> 01:04:28,573
Show me what he likes.

1484
01:04:29,156 --> 01:04:30,533
"Put-together"?

1485
01:04:30,616 --> 01:04:31,784
"White shirt"?

1486
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:34,203
"Tomato pasta."

1487
01:04:34,287 --> 01:04:38,291
Oh, this is
too much information flooding in.

1488
01:04:40,668 --> 01:04:43,045
"Her food…"

1489
01:04:48,175 --> 01:04:49,594
That was not enough time.

1490
01:04:59,937 --> 01:05:02,064
-The first one. She's back.
-She's here.

1491
01:05:02,148 --> 01:05:04,275
It was so much fun.

1492
01:05:04,358 --> 01:05:05,651
-So much fun.
-Did you have fun?

1493
01:05:05,735 --> 01:05:06,986
Yes, I did.

1494
01:05:07,987 --> 01:05:10,364
Five minutes passed so quickly.

1495
01:05:10,448 --> 01:05:12,992
I was enjoying it so much,

1496
01:05:13,075 --> 01:05:15,578
then when I checked the clock,
only 1 minute and 30 seconds remained.

1497
01:05:15,661 --> 01:05:16,829
So I went, "What?"

1498
01:05:17,705 --> 01:05:19,498
-"No!"
-I'm curious.

1499
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:22,168
I hurried back for some toast.

1500
01:05:23,461 --> 01:05:25,504
-The questions were hard.
-Yeah, they were.

1501
01:05:25,588 --> 01:05:26,839
Seriously.

1502
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:33,387
<i>In the 5 Minute Library,</i>

1503
01:05:33,471 --> 01:05:36,432
<i>I learned that he gets butterflies</i>
<i>in his stomach</i>

1504
01:05:36,515 --> 01:05:38,684
<i>when a woman scoops out</i>

1505
01:05:38,768 --> 01:05:40,519
<i>some of her food for him to try.</i>

1506
01:05:40,603 --> 01:05:42,647
<i>I remember reading that.</i>

1507
01:05:44,398 --> 01:05:46,943
<i>There wasn't a plate for him to use,</i>
<i>so I just asked him</i>

1508
01:05:47,026 --> 01:05:48,319
<i>if he wanted some toast.</i>

1509
01:05:48,402 --> 01:05:50,237
Don't you need to eat? Want some toast?

1510
01:05:50,321 --> 01:05:52,823
I had some cereal earlier. It's okay.

1511
01:05:54,325 --> 01:05:55,576
Hey!

1512
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:57,912
-I mean…
-What's so wrong with having more food?

1513
01:05:57,995 --> 01:06:00,206
Seriously, he's so annoying.

1514
01:06:00,289 --> 01:06:01,958
Men always say it's okay.

1515
01:06:02,041 --> 01:06:03,751
-"Do you want a hand warmer?"
-"It's okay."

1516
01:06:03,834 --> 01:06:05,461
-"Do you want some toast?"
-"It's okay."

1517
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:08,506
Eat both cereal and toast.
Is that so hard?

1518
01:06:08,589 --> 01:06:09,840
They're two different things,

1519
01:06:09,924 --> 01:06:11,592
-so why say no?
-Season One people were annoying,

1520
01:06:11,676 --> 01:06:13,469
but these guys annoy me too,
in a different way.

1521
01:06:13,552 --> 01:06:15,513
-I know. In different ways.
-They're…

1522
01:06:15,596 --> 01:06:17,390
These guys are a bit more annoying.

1523
01:06:17,473 --> 01:06:18,724
He should've just taken a bite.

1524
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:21,560
Look. If they say, "It's okay,"

1525
01:06:21,644 --> 01:06:23,896
-the woman will think he's not interested.
-Exactly.

1526
01:06:23,980 --> 01:06:25,856
-And she'd feel embarrassed.
-She'd be embarrassed.

1527
01:06:25,940 --> 01:06:28,526
-It leaves the woman speechless.
-Exactly.

1528
01:06:28,609 --> 01:06:30,277
There will be no next chance!

1529
01:06:33,322 --> 01:06:34,281
Seriously…

1530
01:06:42,456 --> 01:06:45,626
<i>I checked Hyuk-joon's diary.</i>

1531
01:06:46,711 --> 01:06:50,840
I wanted to learn
about his ideal type in detail.

1532
01:06:50,923 --> 01:06:53,592
<i>"What does he like?"</i>

1533
01:06:53,676 --> 01:06:55,678
<i>"What makes his heart flutter?"</i>

1534
01:06:55,761 --> 01:06:58,347
<i>I tried to gain such information.</i>

1535
01:07:02,685 --> 01:07:04,353
<i>He gets butterflies</i>

1536
01:07:04,437 --> 01:07:07,273
<i>when a woman removes a lint</i>
<i>from his clothes.</i>

1537
01:07:07,356 --> 01:07:10,735
<i>He likes lowkey physical contact</i>
<i>like that, so…</i>

1538
01:07:11,318 --> 01:07:13,237
<i>I thought I could try that.</i>

1539
01:07:17,366 --> 01:07:18,617
Let me check out Jin-woo's.

1540
01:07:19,201 --> 01:07:20,661
<i>I checked Jin-woo's diary.</i>

1541
01:07:21,203 --> 01:07:22,329
Thirty seconds?

1542
01:07:28,502 --> 01:07:31,505
<i>His answers were very similar to mine.</i>

1543
01:07:32,631 --> 01:07:34,175
<i>Wanting to hear,</i>
<i>"I feel comfortable around you."</i>

1544
01:07:34,258 --> 01:07:36,761
<i>My answer was similar.</i>

1545
01:07:36,844 --> 01:07:39,305
<i>Between the mountain and the ocean,</i>
<i>I chose the ocean.</i>

1546
01:07:39,388 --> 01:07:41,390
<i>Even his reason was similar to mine.</i>

1547
01:07:43,184 --> 01:07:45,478
<i>I kept thinking, "This is fascinating."</i>

1548
01:07:51,776 --> 01:07:54,403
Older women… Three years?

1549
01:07:56,822 --> 01:07:59,283
<i>I was sure he's younger than me.</i>

1550
01:07:59,366 --> 01:08:03,162
<i>So I only focused on what he said</i>
<i>about older women.</i>

1551
01:08:03,788 --> 01:08:05,414
<i>He preferred older women the least.</i>

1552
01:08:05,498 --> 01:08:07,041
THE ORDER OF PREFERENCE
SAME AGE, YOUNGER, OLDER

1553
01:08:07,124 --> 01:08:09,251
<i>I thought, "This is bad."</i>

1554
01:08:10,836 --> 01:08:12,880
"Long, straight hair without bangs"?
I'm screwed.

1555
01:08:13,422 --> 01:08:16,133
<i>His favorite hairstyle was</i>
<i>long, straight hair without bangs.</i>

1556
01:08:16,217 --> 01:08:19,095
But I have short hair with bangs.

1557
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:21,347
And it's not like
I can grow out my hair now.

1558
01:08:21,430 --> 01:08:24,558
I also can't change the fact
that I'm older than him.

1559
01:08:24,642 --> 01:08:27,394
<i>I read his answers thinking,</i>
<i>"What am I going to do?"</i>

1560
01:08:32,775 --> 01:08:34,151
I want to read some more.

1561
01:08:34,777 --> 01:08:37,655
It only left her discouraged.

1562
01:08:37,738 --> 01:08:40,032
5 MINUTE LIBRARY VOUCHER
NEW ETERNAL SINGLES, ENTER THE LIBRARY

1563
01:08:40,116 --> 01:08:43,494
<i>There was a coupon</i>
<i>and a key to the 5 Minute Library.</i>

1564
01:08:44,328 --> 01:08:47,498
<i>I grabbed Hyuk-joon's diary</i>
<i>because he stood out the most.</i>

1565
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:51,043
<i>I read Su-ji's diary.</i>

1566
01:08:58,342 --> 01:08:59,969
Hey, whose diary did you read?

1567
01:09:00,678 --> 01:09:02,638
-Whose diary did you read?
-How about you?

1568
01:09:02,721 --> 01:09:04,181
I read Jin-woo's.

1569
01:09:04,265 --> 01:09:06,142
-I read Jung-yun's.
-What?

1570
01:09:06,225 --> 01:09:08,394
I checked which hairstyle he liked.

1571
01:09:08,477 --> 01:09:10,646
He likes long, straight hair
without bangs.

1572
01:09:10,729 --> 01:09:11,730
What?

1573
01:09:12,690 --> 01:09:14,066
You're the exact opposite.

1574
01:09:15,526 --> 01:09:16,777
Oh, no.

1575
01:09:18,362 --> 01:09:19,655
-Hey.
-What should I do?

1576
01:09:19,738 --> 01:09:21,782
Wig. Wear a wig.

1577
01:09:21,866 --> 01:09:23,826
-Give me some of your hair.
-You need a wig.

1578
01:09:23,909 --> 01:09:25,995
Get yourself a wig right away.

1579
01:09:26,078 --> 01:09:27,788
Do you want to borrow my hair?

1580
01:09:27,872 --> 01:09:29,039
Cut me some of your hair.

1581
01:09:29,957 --> 01:09:32,209
As soon as I read that answer,

1582
01:09:32,293 --> 01:09:34,044
I thought, "This is bad."

1583
01:09:35,713 --> 01:09:39,633
Just as you didn't care about his height,
you could change his mind too.

1584
01:09:39,717 --> 01:09:41,886
-That's only his preference.
-Right.

1585
01:09:41,969 --> 01:09:44,471
If you guys click,
he could change his mind.

1586
01:09:44,555 --> 01:09:45,806
Just flip it over.

1587
01:09:45,890 --> 01:09:46,932
Boom! Flip it over.

1588
01:09:47,016 --> 01:09:48,934
Go, "Boom!"

1589
01:09:49,018 --> 01:09:50,519
-Let's go. The others are waiting.
-Okay.

1590
01:09:50,603 --> 01:09:54,064
CHOI HYUN-SEO
LEE HAN-JU

1591
01:09:55,649 --> 01:09:58,694
-Jin-woo is wearing glasses today.
-Right.

1592
01:09:58,777 --> 01:10:03,490
I wonder what Soo-hyun will think
about him in glasses.

1593
01:10:03,574 --> 01:10:04,825
Soo-hyun? I'm curious too.

1594
01:10:04,909 --> 01:10:06,493
I told him to wear them because I thought

1595
01:10:06,577 --> 01:10:07,995
-they'd look good on him.
-They do.

1596
01:10:08,078 --> 01:10:10,623
A MOMENT AGO

1597
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:12,958
-You have good eyesight, right?
-Yes.

1598
01:10:13,042 --> 01:10:15,085
I used to wear glasses.
But I got laser eye surgery.

1599
01:10:16,086 --> 01:10:17,421
I used to wear glasses.

1600
01:10:17,504 --> 01:10:18,464
Horn-rimmed ones.

1601
01:10:19,131 --> 01:10:21,425
-They suit you. Keep them on.
-Yeah, you look good.

1602
01:10:26,055 --> 01:10:27,056
Throw them on.

1603
01:10:27,681 --> 01:10:28,557
"Throw"?

1604
01:10:32,144 --> 01:10:35,564
Jin-woo resembles Lai Kuan-lin the most.

1605
01:10:37,858 --> 01:10:38,943
Lai Kuan-lin…

1606
01:10:39,026 --> 01:10:41,320
-He's handsome.
-That's a hot take.

1607
01:10:41,403 --> 01:10:42,863
Lai Kuan-lin's fans will go,

1608
01:10:43,781 --> 01:10:45,532
"Lai Kuan-lin? Are you serious?"

1609
01:10:45,616 --> 01:10:49,578
They'll pounce on me
for saying, "He looks like Young K"

1610
01:10:49,662 --> 01:10:51,872
-and "He looks like Lai Kuan-lin."
-But he does resemble Young K.

1611
01:10:53,207 --> 01:10:57,127
Tae-hoon looked
more like Young K yesterday.

1612
01:10:57,211 --> 01:11:00,214
Today, he looks softer.

1613
01:11:00,297 --> 01:11:02,258
Maybe because
I've grown familiar with him.

1614
01:11:02,341 --> 01:11:03,509
He's beginning to look

1615
01:11:04,260 --> 01:11:05,219
less like the singer.

1616
01:11:05,844 --> 01:11:06,971
Less like Young K?

1617
01:11:07,596 --> 01:11:08,722
I agree.

1618
01:11:09,306 --> 01:11:11,892
But Jin-woo never resembled
Lai Kuan-lin, period.

1619
01:11:12,977 --> 01:11:14,436
He does!

1620
01:11:14,520 --> 01:11:16,981
Said the women blinded by love.

1621
01:11:17,064 --> 01:11:18,357
"He looks like Lai Kuan-lin!"

1622
01:11:18,440 --> 01:11:20,150
I stand by my point.

1623
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:23,153
Finally.

1624
01:11:24,029 --> 01:11:27,157
Let's gather around
at the Eternal Singles' Yard.

1625
01:11:27,241 --> 01:11:29,910
One-on-One Date.

1626
01:11:29,994 --> 01:11:32,955
Finally, the first
One-on-One Date outside.

1627
01:11:33,580 --> 01:11:34,581
How will it go?

1628
01:11:39,044 --> 01:11:41,588
What? "Please Find My Item."

1629
01:11:41,672 --> 01:11:43,215
<i>-That's a classic.</i>
<i>-A classic.</i>

1630
01:11:43,299 --> 01:11:44,508
<i>-Nice.</i>
<i>-Great.</i>

1631
01:11:47,720 --> 01:11:51,557
<i>The items show why</i>
<i>the male participants are eternal singles.</i>

1632
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:53,267
<i>Women could figure it out.</i>

1633
01:11:53,350 --> 01:11:55,019
<i>It's all about using your wits.</i>

1634
01:11:55,102 --> 01:11:57,104
I just caught a glimpse

1635
01:11:57,187 --> 01:11:59,440
-of an item that gave me goosebumps.
-I did too.

1636
01:11:59,523 --> 01:12:00,774
-That one?
-Which one?

1637
01:12:01,734 --> 01:12:03,485
-It's a dental implant.
-Yes.

1638
01:12:03,569 --> 01:12:04,653
I wasn't mistaken, right?

1639
01:12:04,737 --> 01:12:05,988
It's scary.

1640
01:12:07,239 --> 01:12:09,825
I'm confused about the scissors
and the book.

1641
01:12:10,659 --> 01:12:12,703
Whose item is <i>The Art of Loving</i>?

1642
01:12:12,786 --> 01:12:14,371
What are those scissors?

1643
01:12:14,455 --> 01:12:15,998
-I know.
-The scissors are…

1644
01:12:16,582 --> 01:12:17,708
Why scissors?

1645
01:12:18,250 --> 01:12:20,586
I don't even know
what that item in the middle is.

1646
01:12:21,378 --> 01:12:22,546
It's a metronome.

1647
01:12:30,846 --> 01:12:34,058
<i>I hoped Su-ji would pick my item.</i>

1648
01:12:35,100 --> 01:12:38,479
<i>She left such a strong first impression.</i>

1649
01:12:41,065 --> 01:12:43,442
So I wanted to talk to her.

1650
01:12:44,735 --> 01:12:47,196
<i>But I spent a lot of time with Soo-hyun,</i>

1651
01:12:48,781 --> 01:12:51,825
<i>and I never got to interact with Su-ji.</i>

1652
01:12:56,497 --> 01:12:58,874
There's a hand warmer behind the cushion.

1653
01:12:59,458 --> 01:13:02,544
<i>It was lowkey,</i>
<i>but Jin-woo was looking after her.</i>

1654
01:13:03,420 --> 01:13:06,965
So I hoped that Su-ji would pick my item.

1655
01:13:08,092 --> 01:13:09,051
<i>I've wanted to</i>

1656
01:13:09,843 --> 01:13:12,930
<i>go on a date with Su-ji.</i>

1657
01:13:13,972 --> 01:13:16,558
<i>She picked me as the person</i>
<i>who left the best first impression</i>

1658
01:13:16,642 --> 01:13:19,269
<i>and gave me a red towel.</i>

1659
01:13:19,853 --> 01:13:23,190
<i>Since then, I've wanted to</i>
<i>ask her about it.</i>

1660
01:13:25,442 --> 01:13:28,570
<i>I hoped Su-ji would pick mine.</i>

1661
01:13:29,488 --> 01:13:31,698
Partner dancing would've been hideous.

1662
01:13:31,782 --> 01:13:33,450
I wouldn't have wanted to do that.

1663
01:13:33,534 --> 01:13:34,743
I guess we were hideous.

1664
01:13:36,078 --> 01:13:40,082
<i>To make up for last evening's blunder,</i>

1665
01:13:41,041 --> 01:13:43,460
<i>I checked Su-ji's diary at the library.</i>

1666
01:13:44,253 --> 01:13:45,671
I wanted to go on a date with Su-ji.

1667
01:13:47,464 --> 01:13:49,174
<i>Su-ji is so popular.</i>

1668
01:13:58,600 --> 01:13:59,560
I pick this.

1669
01:15:02,664 --> 01:15:04,666
Subtitle translation by: Dongjoo Park
